@graph.rdfs:comment: Event type: Festival.

@graph.rdfs:label: FilmAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of capturing sound and moving images on film, video, or digitally.

@graph.rdfs:label: FinancialProduct
@graph.rdfs:comment: A product provided to consumers and businesses by financial institutions such as banks, insurance companies, brokerage firms, consumer finance companies, and investment companies which comprise the financial services industry.

@graph.rdfs:label: FinancialService
@graph.rdfs:comment: Financial services business.

@graph.rdfs:label: FindAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of finding an object.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[SearchAction]]: FindAction is generally lead by a SearchAction, but not necessarily.

@graph.rdfs:label: FireStation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A fire station. With firemen.

@graph.rdfs:label: Flight
@graph.rdfs:comment: An airline flight.

@graph.rdfs:label: FlightReservation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A reservation for air travel.\\n\\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

@graph.rdfs:label: Float
@graph.rdfs:comment: Data type: Floating number.

@graph.rdfs:label: Florist
@graph.rdfs:comment: A florist.

@graph.rdfs:label: FollowAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of forming a personal connection with someone/something (object) unidirectionally/asymmetrically to get updates polled from.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[BefriendAction]]: Unlike BefriendAction, FollowAction implies that the connection is *not* necessarily reciprocal.\\n* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, FollowAction implies that the follower acts as an active agent constantly/actively polling for updates.\\n* [[RegisterAction]]: Unlike RegisterAction, FollowAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.\\n* [[JoinAction]]: Unlike JoinAction, FollowAction implies that the agent is interested in getting updates from the object.\\n* [[TrackAction]]: Unlike TrackAction, FollowAction refers to the polling of updates of all aspects of animate objects rather than the location of inanimate objects (e.g. you track a package, but you don't follow it).

@graph.rdfs:label: FoodEstablishment
@graph.rdfs:comment: A food-related business.

@graph.rdfs:label: FoodEstablishmentReservation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A reservation to dine at a food-related business.\\n\\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

@graph.rdfs:label: FoodEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: Event type: Food event.

@graph.rdfs:label: FoodService
@graph.rdfs:comment: A food service, like breakfast, lunch, or dinner.

@graph.rdfs:label: FurnitureStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A furniture store.

@graph.rdfs:label: Game
@graph.rdfs:comment: The Game type represents things which are games. These are typically rule-governed recreational activities, e.g. role-playing games in which players assume the role of characters in a fictional setting.

@graph.rdfs:label: GamePlayMode
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.

@graph.rdfs:label: GameServer
@graph.rdfs:comment: Server that provides game interaction in a multiplayer game.

@graph.rdfs:label: GameServerStatus
@graph.rdfs:comment: Status of a game server.

@graph.rdfs:label: GardenStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A garden store.

@graph.rdfs:label: GasStation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A gas station.

@graph.rdfs:label: GatedResidenceCommunity
@graph.rdfs:comment: Residence type: Gated community.

@graph.rdfs:label: GenderType
@graph.rdfs:comment: An enumeration of genders.

@graph.rdfs:label: GeneralContractor
@graph.rdfs:comment: A general contractor.

@graph.rdfs:label: GeoCoordinates
@graph.rdfs:comment: The geographic coordinates of a place or event.

@graph.rdfs:label: GeoShape
@graph.rdfs:comment: The geographic shape of a place. A GeoShape can be described using several properties whose values are based on latitude/longitude pairs. Either whitespace or commas can be used to separate latitude and longitude; whitespace should be used when writing a list of several such points.

@graph.rdfs:label: GiveAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of transferring ownership of an object to a destination. Reciprocal of TakeAction.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[TakeAction]]: Reciprocal of GiveAction.\\n* [[SendAction]]: Unlike SendAction, GiveAction implies that ownership is being transferred (e.g. I may send my laptop to you, but that doesn't mean I'm giving it to you).

@graph.rdfs:label: GolfCourse
@graph.rdfs:comment: A golf course.

@graph.rdfs:label: GovernmentBuilding
@graph.rdfs:comment: A government building.

@graph.rdfs:label: GovernmentOffice
@graph.rdfs:comment: A government office—for example, an IRS or DMV office.

@graph.rdfs:label: GovernmentOrganization
@graph.rdfs:comment: A governmental organization or agency.

@graph.rdfs:label: GovernmentPermit
@graph.rdfs:comment: A permit issued by a government agency.

@graph.rdfs:label: GovernmentService
@graph.rdfs:comment: A service provided by a government organization, e.g. food stamps, veterans benefits, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: GroceryStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A grocery store.

@graph.rdfs:label: HVACBusiness
@graph.rdfs:comment: A business that provides Heating, Ventilation and Air Conditioning services.

@graph.rdfs:label: HairSalon
@graph.rdfs:comment: A hair salon.

@graph.rdfs:label: HardwareStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A hardware store.

@graph.rdfs:label: HealthAndBeautyBusiness
@graph.rdfs:comment: Health and beauty.

@graph.rdfs:label: HealthClub
@graph.rdfs:comment: A health club.

@graph.rdfs:label: HighSchool
@graph.rdfs:comment: A high school.

@graph.rdfs:label: HinduTemple
@graph.rdfs:comment: A Hindu temple.

@graph.rdfs:label: HobbyShop
@graph.rdfs:comment: A store that sells materials useful or necessary for various hobbies.

@graph.rdfs:label: HomeAndConstructionBusiness
@graph.rdfs:comment: A construction business.\\n\\nA HomeAndConstructionBusiness is a [[LocalBusiness]] that provides services around homes and buildings.\\n\\nAs a [[LocalBusiness]] it can be described as a [[provider]] of one or more [[Service]]\\(s).

@graph.rdfs:label: HomeGoodsStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A home goods store.

@graph.rdfs:label: Hospital
@graph.rdfs:comment: A hospital.

@graph.rdfs:label: House
@graph.rdfs:comment: A house is a building or structure that has the ability to be occupied for habitation by humans or other creatures (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see <a href=\

@graph.rdfs:label: HousePainter
@graph.rdfs:comment: A house painting service.

@graph.rdfs:label: HowTo
@graph.rdfs:comment: Instructions that explain how to achieve a result by performing a sequence of steps.

@graph.rdfs:label: HowToDirection
@graph.rdfs:comment: A direction indicating a single action to do in the instructions for how to achieve a result.

@graph.rdfs:label: HowToItem
@graph.rdfs:comment: An item used as either a tool or supply when performing the instructions for how to achieve a result.

@graph.rdfs:label: HowToSection
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub-grouping of steps in the instructions for how to achieve a result (e.g. steps for making a pie crust within a pie recipe).

@graph.rdfs:label: HowToStep
@graph.rdfs:comment: A step in the instructions for how to achieve a result. It is an ordered list with HowToDirection and/or HowToTip items.

@graph.rdfs:label: HowToSupply
@graph.rdfs:comment: A supply consumed when performing the instructions for how to achieve a result.

@graph.rdfs:label: HowToTip
@graph.rdfs:comment: An explanation in the instructions for how to achieve a result. It provides supplementary information about a technique, supply, author's preference, etc. It can explain what could be done, or what should not be done, but doesn't specify what should be done (see HowToDirection).

@graph.rdfs:label: HowToTool
@graph.rdfs:comment: A tool used (but not consumed) when performing instructions for how to achieve a result.

@graph.rdfs:label: IceCreamShop
@graph.rdfs:comment: An ice cream shop.

@graph.rdfs:label: IgnoreAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of intentionally disregarding the object. An agent ignores an object.

@graph.rdfs:label: ImageGallery
@graph.rdfs:comment: Web page type: Image gallery page.

@graph.rdfs:label: ImageObject
@graph.rdfs:comment: An image file.

@graph.rdfs:label: IndividualProduct
@graph.rdfs:comment: A single, identifiable product instance (e.g. a laptop with a particular serial number).

@graph.rdfs:label: InformAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of notifying someone of information pertinent to them, with no expectation of a response.

@graph.rdfs:label: InsertAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of adding at a specific location in an ordered collection.

@graph.rdfs:label: InstallAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of installing an application.

@graph.rdfs:label: InsuranceAgency
@graph.rdfs:comment: An Insurance agency.

@graph.rdfs:label: Intangible
@graph.rdfs:comment: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things such as quantities, structured values, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: Integer
@graph.rdfs:comment: Data type: Integer.

@graph.rdfs:label: InteractAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of interacting with another person or organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: InteractionCounter
@graph.rdfs:comment: A summary of how users have interacted with this CreativeWork. In most cases, authors will use a subtype to specify the specific type of interaction.

@graph.rdfs:label: InternetCafe
@graph.rdfs:comment: An internet cafe.

@graph.rdfs:label: InvestmentOrDeposit
@graph.rdfs:comment: A type of financial product that typically requires the client to transfer funds to a financial service in return for potential beneficial financial return.

@graph.rdfs:label: InviteAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of asking someone to attend an event. Reciprocal of RsvpAction.

@graph.rdfs:label: Invoice
@graph.rdfs:comment: A statement of the money due for goods or services; a bill.

@graph.rdfs:label: ItemAvailability
@graph.rdfs:comment: A list of possible product availability options.

@graph.rdfs:label: ItemList
@graph.rdfs:comment: A list of items of any sort—for example, Top 10 Movies About Weathermen, or Top 100 Party Songs. Not to be confused with HTML lists, which are often used only for formatting.

@graph.rdfs:label: ItemListOrderType
@graph.rdfs:comment: Enumerated for values for itemListOrder for indicating how an ordered ItemList is organized.

@graph.rdfs:label: ItemPage
@graph.rdfs:comment: A page devoted to a single item, such as a particular product or hotel.

@graph.rdfs:label: JewelryStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A jewelry store.

@graph.rdfs:label: JobPosting
@graph.rdfs:comment: A listing that describes a job opening in a certain organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: JoinAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: An agent joins an event/group with participants/friends at a location.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[RegisterAction]]: Unlike RegisterAction, JoinAction refers to joining a group/team of people.\\n* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be receiving updates.\\n* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be polling for updates.

@graph.rdfs:label: LakeBodyOfWater
@graph.rdfs:comment: A lake (for example, Lake Pontrachain).

@graph.rdfs:label: Landform
@graph.rdfs:comment: A landform or physical feature.  Landform elements include mountains, plains, lakes, rivers, seascape and oceanic waterbody interface features such as bays, peninsulas, seas and so forth, including sub-aqueous terrain features such as submersed mountain ranges, volcanoes, and the great ocean basins.

@graph.rdfs:label: LandmarksOrHistoricalBuildings
@graph.rdfs:comment: An historical landmark or building.

@graph.rdfs:label: Language
@graph.rdfs:comment: Natural languages such as Spanish, Tamil, Hindi, English, etc. Formal language code tags expressed in [BCP 47](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IETF_language_tag) can be used via the [[alternateName]] property. The Language type previously also covered programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, which are now best represented using [[ComputerLanguage]].

@graph.rdfs:label: LeaveAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: An agent leaves an event / group with participants/friends at a location.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[JoinAction]]: The antonym of LeaveAction.\\n* [[UnRegisterAction]]: Unlike UnRegisterAction, LeaveAction implies leaving a group/team of people rather than a service.

@graph.rdfs:label: LegalService
@graph.rdfs:comment: A LegalService is a business that provides legally-oriented services, advice and representation, e.g. law firms.\\n\\nAs a [[LocalBusiness]] it can be described as a [[provider]] of one or more [[Service]]\\(s).

@graph.rdfs:label: LegislativeBuilding
@graph.rdfs:comment: A legislative building—for example, the state capitol.

@graph.rdfs:label: LendAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of providing an object under an agreement that it will be returned at a later date. Reciprocal of BorrowAction.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[BorrowAction]]: Reciprocal of LendAction.

@graph.rdfs:label: Library
@graph.rdfs:comment: A library.

@graph.rdfs:label: LikeAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of expressing a positive sentiment about the object. An agent likes an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

@graph.rdfs:label: LiquorStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A shop that sells alcoholic drinks such as wine, beer, whisky and other spirits.

@graph.rdfs:label: ListItem
@graph.rdfs:comment: An list item, e.g. a step in a checklist or how-to description.

@graph.rdfs:label: ListenAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of consuming audio content.

@graph.rdfs:label: LiteraryEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: Event type: Literary event.

@graph.rdfs:label: LiveBlogPosting
@graph.rdfs:comment: A [[LiveBlogPosting]] is a [[BlogPosting]] intended to provide a rolling textual coverage of an ongoing event through continuous updates.

@graph.rdfs:label: LoanOrCredit
@graph.rdfs:comment: A financial product for the loaning of an amount of money, or line of credit, under agreed terms and charges.

@graph.rdfs:label: LocalBusiness
@graph.rdfs:comment: A particular physical business or branch of an organization. Examples of LocalBusiness include a restaurant, a particular branch of a restaurant chain, a branch of a bank, a medical practice, a club, a bowling alley, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: LocationFeatureSpecification
@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies a location feature by providing a structured value representing a feature of an accommodation as a property-value pair of varying degrees of formality.

@graph.rdfs:label: Locksmith
@graph.rdfs:comment: A locksmith.

@graph.rdfs:label: LodgingBusiness
@graph.rdfs:comment: A lodging business, such as a motel, hotel, or inn.

@graph.rdfs:label: LodgingReservation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A reservation for lodging at a hotel, motel, inn, etc.\\n\\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

@graph.rdfs:label: LoseAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of being defeated in a competitive activity.

@graph.rdfs:label: Map
@graph.rdfs:comment: A map.

@graph.rdfs:label: MapCategoryType
@graph.rdfs:comment: An enumeration of several kinds of Map.

@graph.rdfs:label: MarryAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of marrying a person.

@graph.rdfs:label: Mass
@graph.rdfs:comment: Properties that take Mass as values are of the form '<Number> <Mass unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 kg'.

@graph.rdfs:label: MediaGallery
@graph.rdfs:comment: Web page type: Media gallery page. A mixed-media page that can contain media such as images, videos, and other multimedia.

@graph.rdfs:label: MediaObject
@graph.rdfs:comment: A media object, such as an image, video, audio, or text object embedded in a web page or a downloadable dataset i.e. DataDownload. Note that a creative work may have many media objects associated with it on the same web page. For example, a page about a single song (MusicRecording) may have a music video (VideoObject), and a high and low bandwidth audio stream (2 AudioObject's).

@graph.rdfs:label: MediaSubscription
@graph.rdfs:comment: A subscription which allows a user to access media including audio, video, books, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: MedicalOrganization
@graph.rdfs:comment: A medical organization (physical or not), such as hospital, institution or clinic.

@graph.rdfs:label: MensClothingStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A men's clothing store.

@graph.rdfs:label: Menu
@graph.rdfs:comment: A structured representation of food or drink items available from a FoodEstablishment.

@graph.rdfs:label: MenuItem
@graph.rdfs:comment: A food or drink item listed in a menu or menu section.

@graph.rdfs:label: MenuSection
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub-grouping of food or drink items in a menu. E.g. courses (such as 'Dinner', 'Breakfast', etc.), specific type of dishes (such as 'Meat', 'Vegan', 'Drinks', etc.), or some other classification made by the menu provider.

@graph.rdfs:label: Message
@graph.rdfs:comment: A single message from a sender to one or more organizations or people.

@graph.rdfs:label: MiddleSchool
@graph.rdfs:comment: A middle school (typically for children aged around 11-14, although this varies somewhat).

@graph.rdfs:label: MobileApplication
@graph.rdfs:comment: A software application designed specifically to work well on a mobile device such as a telephone.

@graph.rdfs:label: MobilePhoneStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A store that sells mobile phones and related accessories.

@graph.rdfs:label: MonetaryAmount
@graph.rdfs:comment: A monetary value or range. This type can be used to describe an amount of money such as $50 USD, or a range as in describing a bank account being suitable for a balance between £1,000 and £1,000,000 GBP, or the value of a salary, etc. It is recommended to use [[PriceSpecification]] Types to describe the price of an Offer, Invoice, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: MonetaryAmountDistribution
@graph.rdfs:comment: A statistical distribution of monetary amounts.

@graph.rdfs:label: Mosque
@graph.rdfs:comment: A mosque.

@graph.rdfs:label: MotorcycleDealer
@graph.rdfs:comment: A motorcycle dealer.

@graph.rdfs:label: MotorcycleRepair
@graph.rdfs:comment: A motorcycle repair shop.

@graph.rdfs:label: Mountain
@graph.rdfs:comment: A mountain, like Mount Whitney or Mount Everest.

@graph.rdfs:label: MoveAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of an agent relocating to a place.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[TransferAction]]: Unlike TransferAction, the subject of the move is a living Person or Organization rather than an inanimate object.

@graph.rdfs:label: Movie
@graph.rdfs:comment: A movie.

@graph.rdfs:label: MovieClip
@graph.rdfs:comment: A short segment/part of a movie.

@graph.rdfs:label: MovieRentalStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A movie rental store.

@graph.rdfs:label: MovieSeries
@graph.rdfs:comment: A series of movies. Included movies can be indicated with the hasPart property.

@graph.rdfs:label: MovieTheater
@graph.rdfs:comment: A movie theater.

@graph.rdfs:label: MovingCompany
@graph.rdfs:comment: A moving company.

@graph.rdfs:label: Museum
@graph.rdfs:comment: A museum.

@graph.rdfs:label: MusicAlbum
@graph.rdfs:comment: A collection of music tracks.

@graph.rdfs:label: MusicAlbumProductionType
@graph.rdfs:comment: Classification of the album by its type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: MusicAlbumReleaseType
@graph.rdfs:comment: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

@graph.rdfs:label: MusicComposition
@graph.rdfs:comment: A musical composition.

@graph.rdfs:label: MusicEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: Event type: Music event.

@graph.rdfs:label: MusicGroup
@graph.rdfs:comment: A musical group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a choir. Can also be a solo musician.

@graph.rdfs:label: MusicPlaylist
@graph.rdfs:comment: A collection of music tracks in playlist form.

@graph.rdfs:label: MusicRecording
@graph.rdfs:comment: A music recording (track), usually a single song.

@graph.rdfs:label: MusicRelease
@graph.rdfs:comment: A MusicRelease is a specific release of a music album.

@graph.rdfs:label: MusicReleaseFormatType
@graph.rdfs:comment: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, i.e. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

@graph.rdfs:label: MusicStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A music store.

@graph.rdfs:label: MusicVenue
@graph.rdfs:comment: A music venue.

@graph.rdfs:label: MusicVideoObject
@graph.rdfs:comment: A music video file.

@graph.rdfs:label: NGO
@graph.rdfs:comment: Organization: Non-governmental Organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: NailSalon
@graph.rdfs:comment: A nail salon.

@graph.rdfs:label: NightClub
@graph.rdfs:comment: A nightclub or discotheque.

@graph.rdfs:label: Notary
@graph.rdfs:comment: A notary.

@graph.rdfs:label: NoteDigitalDocument
@graph.rdfs:comment: A file containing a note, primarily for the author.

@graph.rdfs:label: NutritionInformation
@graph.rdfs:comment: Nutritional information about the recipe.

@graph.rdfs:label: Occupation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A profession, may involve prolonged training and/or a formal qualification.

@graph.rdfs:label: OceanBodyOfWater
@graph.rdfs:comment: An ocean (for example, the Pacific).

@graph.rdfs:label: Offer
@graph.rdfs:comment: An offer to transfer some rights to an item or to provide a service — for example, an offer to sell tickets to an event, to rent the DVD of a movie, to stream a TV show over the internet, to repair a motorcycle, or to loan a book.\\n\\nNote: As the [[businessFunction]] property, which identifies the form of offer (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose), defaults to http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell; an Offer without a defined businessFunction value can be assumed to be an offer to sell.\\n\\nFor [GTIN](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin)-related fields, see [Check Digit calculator](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/support/check_digit_calculator) and [validation guide](http://www.gs1us.org/resources/standards/gtin-validation-guide) from [GS1](http://www.gs1.org/).

@graph.rdfs:label: OfferCatalog
@graph.rdfs:comment: An OfferCatalog is an ItemList that contains related Offers and/or further OfferCatalogs that are offeredBy the same provider.

@graph.rdfs:label: OfferItemCondition
@graph.rdfs:comment: A list of possible conditions for the item.

@graph.rdfs:label: OfficeEquipmentStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: An office equipment store.

@graph.rdfs:label: OnDemandEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: A publication event, e.g. catch-up TV or radio podcast, during which a program is available on-demand.

@graph.rdfs:label: Order
@graph.rdfs:comment: An order is a confirmation of a transaction (a receipt), which can contain multiple line items, each represented by an Offer that has been accepted by the customer.

@graph.rdfs:label: OrderAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: An agent orders an object/product/service to be delivered/sent.

@graph.rdfs:label: OrderItem
@graph.rdfs:comment: An order item is a line of an order. It includes the quantity and shipping details of a bought offer.

@graph.rdfs:label: OrderStatus
@graph.rdfs:comment: Enumerated status values for Order.

@graph.rdfs:label: Organization
@graph.rdfs:comment: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: OrganizationRole
@graph.rdfs:comment: A subclass of Role used to describe roles within organizations.

@graph.rdfs:label: OrganizeAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of manipulating/administering/supervising/controlling one or more objects.

@graph.rdfs:label: OutletStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: An outlet store.

@graph.rdfs:label: OwnershipInfo
@graph.rdfs:comment: A structured value providing information about when a certain organization or person owned a certain product.

@graph.rdfs:label: PaintAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of producing a painting, typically with paint and canvas as instruments.

@graph.rdfs:label: Painting
@graph.rdfs:comment: A painting.

@graph.rdfs:label: ParcelDelivery
@graph.rdfs:comment: The delivery of a parcel either via the postal service or a commercial service.

@graph.rdfs:label: ParentAudience
@graph.rdfs:comment: A set of characteristics describing parents, who can be interested in viewing some content.

@graph.rdfs:label: Park
@graph.rdfs:comment: A park.

@graph.rdfs:label: ParkingFacility
@graph.rdfs:comment: A parking lot or other parking facility.

@graph.rdfs:label: PawnShop
@graph.rdfs:comment: A shop that will buy, or lend money against the security of, personal possessions.

@graph.rdfs:label: PayAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: An agent pays a price to a participant.

@graph.rdfs:label: PaymentCard
@graph.rdfs:comment: A payment method using a credit, debit, store or other card to associate the payment with an account.

@graph.rdfs:label: PaymentChargeSpecification
@graph.rdfs:comment: The costs of settling the payment using a particular payment method.

@graph.rdfs:label: PaymentService
@graph.rdfs:comment: A Service to transfer funds from a person or organization to a beneficiary person or organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: PaymentStatusType
@graph.rdfs:comment: A specific payment status. For example, PaymentDue, PaymentComplete, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: PeopleAudience
@graph.rdfs:comment: A set of characteristics belonging to people, e.g. who compose an item's target audience.

@graph.rdfs:label: PerformAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of participating in performance arts.

@graph.rdfs:label: PerformanceRole
@graph.rdfs:comment: A PerformanceRole is a Role that some entity places with regard to a theatrical performance, e.g. in a Movie, TVSeries etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: PerformingArtsTheater
@graph.rdfs:comment: A theater or other performing art center.

@graph.rdfs:label: PerformingGroup
@graph.rdfs:comment: A performance group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a circus.

@graph.rdfs:label: Periodical
@graph.rdfs:comment: A publication in any medium issued in successive parts bearing numerical or chronological designations and intended to continue indefinitely, such as a magazine, scholarly journal, or newspaper.\\n\\nSee also [blog post](https://blog.schema.org/2014/09/02/schema-org-support-for-bibliographic-relationships-and-periodicals/).

@graph.rdfs:label: Permit
@graph.rdfs:comment: A permit issued by an organization, e.g. a parking pass.

@graph.rdfs:label: Person
@graph.rdfs:comment: A person (alive, dead, undead, or fictional).

@graph.rdfs:label: PetStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A pet store.

@graph.rdfs:label: Pharmacy
@graph.rdfs:comment: A pharmacy or drugstore.

@graph.rdfs:label: Photograph
@graph.rdfs:comment: A photograph.

@graph.rdfs:label: PhotographAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of capturing still images of objects using a camera.

@graph.rdfs:label: Physician
@graph.rdfs:comment: An individual physician or a physician's office considered as a [[MedicalOrganization]].

@graph.rdfs:label: Place
@graph.rdfs:comment: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.

@graph.rdfs:label: PlaceOfWorship
@graph.rdfs:comment: Place of worship, such as a church, synagogue, or mosque.

@graph.rdfs:label: PlanAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of planning the execution of an event/task/action/reservation/plan to a future date.

@graph.rdfs:label: PlayAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of playing/exercising/training/performing for enjoyment, leisure, recreation, competition or exercise.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[ListenAction]]: Unlike ListenAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to performing for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming music.\\n* [[WatchAction]]: Unlike WatchAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to showing/displaying for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming visual content.

@graph.rdfs:label: Playground
@graph.rdfs:comment: A playground.

@graph.rdfs:label: Plumber
@graph.rdfs:comment: A plumbing service.

@graph.rdfs:label: PoliceStation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A police station.

@graph.rdfs:label: PoliticalParty
@graph.rdfs:comment: Organization: Political Party.

@graph.rdfs:label: Pond
@graph.rdfs:comment: A pond.

@graph.rdfs:label: PostOffice
@graph.rdfs:comment: A post office.

@graph.rdfs:label: PostalAddress
@graph.rdfs:comment: The mailing address.

@graph.rdfs:label: PostalCodeRangeSpecification
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates a range of postal codes, usually defined as the set of valid codes between [[postalCodeBegin]] and [[postalCodeEnd]], inclusively.

@graph.rdfs:label: PreOrderAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: An agent orders a (not yet released) object/product/service to be delivered/sent.

@graph.rdfs:label: PrependAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of inserting at the beginning if an ordered collection.

@graph.rdfs:label: Preschool
@graph.rdfs:comment: A preschool.

@graph.rdfs:label: PresentationDigitalDocument
@graph.rdfs:comment: A file containing slides or used for a presentation.

@graph.rdfs:label: PriceSpecification
@graph.rdfs:comment: A structured value representing a price or price range. Typically, only the subclasses of this type are used for markup. It is recommended to use [[MonetaryAmount]] to describe independent amounts of money such as a salary, credit card limits, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: Product
@graph.rdfs:comment: Any offered product or service. For example: a pair of shoes; a concert ticket; the rental of a car; a haircut; or an episode of a TV show streamed online.

@graph.rdfs:label: ProductModel
@graph.rdfs:comment: A datasheet or vendor specification of a product (in the sense of a prototypical description).

@graph.rdfs:label: ProfilePage
@graph.rdfs:comment: Web page type: Profile page.

@graph.rdfs:label: ProgramMembership
@graph.rdfs:comment: Used to describe membership in a loyalty programs (e.g. \

@graph.rdfs:label: PropertyValueSpecification
@graph.rdfs:comment: A Property value specification.

@graph.rdfs:label: PublicSwimmingPool
@graph.rdfs:comment: A public swimming pool.

@graph.rdfs:label: PublicationEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: A PublicationEvent corresponds indifferently to the event of publication for a CreativeWork of any type, e.g. a broadcast event, an on-demand event, a book/journal publication via a variety of delivery media.

@graph.rdfs:label: PublicationIssue
@graph.rdfs:comment: A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or publication volume, often numbered, usually containing a grouping of works such as articles.\\n\\nSee also [blog post](https://blog-schema.org/2014/09/02/schema-org-support-for-bibliographic-relationships-and-periodicals/).

@graph.rdfs:label: PublicationVolume
@graph.rdfs:comment: A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or multi-volume work, often numbered. It may represent a time span, such as a year.\\n\\nSee also [blog post](https://blog-schema.org/2014/09/02/schema-org-support-for-bibliographic-relationships-and-periodicals/).

@graph.rdfs:label: QAPage
@graph.rdfs:comment: A QAPage is a WebPage focussed on a specific Question and its Answer(s), e.g. in a question answering site or documenting Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs).

@graph.rdfs:label: QualitativeValue
@graph.rdfs:comment: A predefined value for a product characteristic, e.g. the power cord plug type 'US' or the garment sizes 'S', 'M', 'L', and 'XL'.

@graph.rdfs:label: QuantitativeValue
@graph.rdfs:comment: A point value or interval for product characteristics and other purposes.

@graph.rdfs:label: QuantitativeValueDistribution
@graph.rdfs:comment: A statistical distribution of values.

@graph.rdfs:label: Quantity
@graph.rdfs:comment: Quantities such as distance, time, mass, weight, etc. Particular instances of say Mass are entities like '3 kg' or '4 milligrams'.

@graph.rdfs:label: Question
@graph.rdfs:comment: A specific question - e.g. from a user seeking answers online, or collected in a Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) document.

@graph.rdfs:label: QuoteAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: An agent quotes/estimates/appraises an object/product/service with a price at a location/store.

@graph.rdfs:label: RVPark
@graph.rdfs:comment: A place offering space for \

@graph.rdfs:label: RadioChannel
@graph.rdfs:comment: A unique instance of a radio BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

@graph.rdfs:label: RadioClip
@graph.rdfs:comment: A short radio program or a segment/part of a radio program.

@graph.rdfs:label: RadioEpisode
@graph.rdfs:comment: A radio episode which can be part of a series or season.

@graph.rdfs:label: RadioSeason
@graph.rdfs:comment: Season dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

@graph.rdfs:label: RadioSeries
@graph.rdfs:comment: CreativeWorkSeries dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

@graph.rdfs:label: RadioStation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A radio station.

@graph.rdfs:label: Rating
@graph.rdfs:comment: A rating is an evaluation on a numeric scale, such as 1 to 5 stars.

@graph.rdfs:label: ReactAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of responding instinctively and emotionally to an object, expressing a sentiment.

@graph.rdfs:label: ReadAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of consuming written content.

@graph.rdfs:label: RealEstateAgent
@graph.rdfs:comment: A real-estate agent.

@graph.rdfs:label: ReceiveAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of physically/electronically taking delivery of an object that has been transferred from an origin to a destination. Reciprocal of SendAction.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[SendAction]]: The reciprocal of ReceiveAction.\\n* [[TakeAction]]: Unlike TakeAction, ReceiveAction does not imply that the ownership has been transferred (e.g. I can receive a package, but it does not mean the package is now mine).

@graph.rdfs:label: Recipe
@graph.rdfs:comment: A recipe. For dietary restrictions covered by the recipe, a few common restrictions are enumerated via [[suitableForDiet]]. The [[keywords]] property can also be used to add more detail.

@graph.rdfs:label: RecyclingCenter
@graph.rdfs:comment: A recycling center.

@graph.rdfs:label: RegisterAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of registering to be a user of a service, product or web page.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[JoinAction]]: Unlike JoinAction, RegisterAction implies you are registering to be a user of a service, *not* a group/team of people.\\n* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting to poll for updates from the object.\\n* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting updates from the object.

@graph.rdfs:label: RejectAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of rejecting to/adopting an object.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[AcceptAction]]: The antonym of RejectAction.

@graph.rdfs:label: RentAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of giving money in return for temporary use, but not ownership, of an object such as a vehicle or property. For example, an agent rents a property from a landlord in exchange for a periodic payment.

@graph.rdfs:label: RentalCarReservation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A reservation for a rental car.\\n\\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

@graph.rdfs:label: ReplaceAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of editing a recipient by replacing an old object with a new object.

@graph.rdfs:label: ReplyAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of responding to a question/message asked/sent by the object. Related to [[AskAction]].\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[AskAction]]: Appears generally as an origin of a ReplyAction.

@graph.rdfs:label: Report
@graph.rdfs:comment: A Report generated by governmental or non-governmental organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: Researcher
@graph.rdfs:comment: Researchers.

@graph.rdfs:label: Reservation
@graph.rdfs:comment: Describes a reservation for travel, dining or an event. Some reservations require tickets. \\n\\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, restaurant reservations, flights, or rental cars, use [[Offer]].

@graph.rdfs:label: ReservationPackage
@graph.rdfs:comment: A group of multiple reservations with common values for all sub-reservations.

@graph.rdfs:label: ReservationStatusType
@graph.rdfs:comment: Enumerated status values for Reservation.

@graph.rdfs:label: ReserveAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: Reserving a concrete object.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[ScheduleAction]]: Unlike ScheduleAction, ReserveAction reserves concrete objects (e.g. a table, a hotel) towards a time slot / spatial allocation.

@graph.rdfs:label: Reservoir
@graph.rdfs:comment: A reservoir of water, typically an artificially created lake, like the Lake Kariba reservoir.

@graph.rdfs:label: Residence
@graph.rdfs:comment: The place where a person lives.

@graph.rdfs:label: Restaurant
@graph.rdfs:comment: A restaurant.

@graph.rdfs:label: RestrictedDiet
@graph.rdfs:comment: A diet restricted to certain foods or preparations for cultural, religious, health or lifestyle reasons.

@graph.rdfs:label: ResumeAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of resuming a device or application which was formerly paused (e.g. resume music playback or resume a timer).

@graph.rdfs:label: ReturnAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of returning to the origin that which was previously received (concrete objects) or taken (ownership).

@graph.rdfs:label: Review
@graph.rdfs:comment: A review of an item - for example, of a restaurant, movie, or store.

@graph.rdfs:label: ReviewAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of producing a balanced opinion about the object for an audience. An agent reviews an object with participants resulting in a review.

@graph.rdfs:label: RiverBodyOfWater
@graph.rdfs:comment: A river (for example, the broad majestic Shannon).

@graph.rdfs:label: Role
@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents additional information about a relationship or property. For example a Role can be used to say that a 'member' role linking some SportsTeam to a player occurred during a particular time period. Or that a Person's 'actor' role in a Movie was for some particular characterName. Such properties can be attached to a Role entity, which is then associated with the main entities using ordinary properties like 'member' or 'actor'.\\n\\nSee also [blog post](https://blog.schema.org/2014/06/16/introducing-role/).

@graph.rdfs:label: RoofingContractor
@graph.rdfs:comment: A roofing contractor.

@graph.rdfs:label: RsvpAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of notifying an event organizer as to whether you expect to attend the event.

@graph.rdfs:label: RsvpResponseType
@graph.rdfs:comment: RsvpResponseType is an enumeration type whose instances represent responding to an RSVP request.

@graph.rdfs:label: SaleEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: Event type: Sales event.

@graph.rdfs:label: ScheduleAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: Scheduling future actions, events, or tasks.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[ReserveAction]]: Unlike ReserveAction, ScheduleAction allocates future actions (e.g. an event, a task, etc) towards a time slot / spatial allocation.

@graph.rdfs:label: ScholarlyArticle
@graph.rdfs:comment: A scholarly article.

@graph.rdfs:label: School
@graph.rdfs:comment: A school.

@graph.rdfs:label: ScreeningEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: A screening of a movie or other video.

@graph.rdfs:label: Sculpture
@graph.rdfs:comment: A piece of sculpture.

@graph.rdfs:label: SeaBodyOfWater
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sea (for example, the Caspian sea).

@graph.rdfs:label: SearchAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of searching for an object.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[FindAction]]: SearchAction generally leads to a FindAction, but not necessarily.

@graph.rdfs:label: SearchResultsPage
@graph.rdfs:comment: Web page type: Search results page.

@graph.rdfs:label: Season
@graph.rdfs:comment: A media season, e.g. TV, radio, video game etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: Seat
@graph.rdfs:comment: Used to describe a seat, such as a reserved seat in an event reservation.

@graph.rdfs:label: SelfStorage
@graph.rdfs:comment: A self-storage facility.

@graph.rdfs:label: SellAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of taking money from a buyer in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent sells an object, product, or service to a buyer for a price. Reciprocal of BuyAction.

@graph.rdfs:label: SendAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of physically/electronically dispatching an object for transfer from an origin to a destination. Related actions:\\n\\n* [[ReceiveAction]]: The reciprocal of SendAction.\\n* [[GiveAction]]: Unlike GiveAction, SendAction does not imply the transfer of ownership (e.g. I can send you my laptop, but I'm not necessarily giving it to you).

@graph.rdfs:label: Series
@graph.rdfs:comment: A Series in schema.org is a group of related items, typically but not necessarily of the same kind. See also [[CreativeWorkSeries]], [[EventSeries]].

@graph.rdfs:label: Service
@graph.rdfs:comment: A service provided by an organization, e.g. delivery service, print services, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: ServiceChannel
@graph.rdfs:comment: A means for accessing a service, e.g. a government office location, web site, or phone number.

@graph.rdfs:label: ShareAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of distributing content to people for their amusement or edification.

@graph.rdfs:label: ShippingDeliveryTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: ShippingDeliveryTime provides various pieces of information about delivery times for shipping.

@graph.rdfs:label: ShippingRateSettings
@graph.rdfs:comment: A ShippingRateSettings represents re-usable pieces of shipping information. It is designed for publication on an URL that may be referenced via the [[shippingSettingsLink]] property of an [[OfferShippingDetails]]. Several occurrences can be published, distinguished and matched (i.e. identified/referenced) by their different values for [[shippingLabel]].

@graph.rdfs:label: ShoeStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A shoe store.

@graph.rdfs:label: ShoppingCenter
@graph.rdfs:comment: A shopping center or mall.

@graph.rdfs:label: SingleFamilyResidence
@graph.rdfs:comment: Residence type: Single-family home.

@graph.rdfs:label: SiteNavigationElement
@graph.rdfs:comment: A navigation element of the page.

@graph.rdfs:label: SkiResort
@graph.rdfs:comment: A ski resort.

@graph.rdfs:label: SocialEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: Event type: Social event.

@graph.rdfs:label: SocialMediaPosting
@graph.rdfs:comment: A post to a social media platform, including blog posts, tweets, Facebook posts, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: SoftwareApplication
@graph.rdfs:comment: A software application.

@graph.rdfs:label: SoftwareSourceCode
@graph.rdfs:comment: Computer programming source code. Example: Full (compile ready) solutions, code snippet samples, scripts, templates.

@graph.rdfs:label: SomeProducts
@graph.rdfs:comment: A placeholder for multiple similar products of the same kind.

@graph.rdfs:label: SpeakableSpecification
@graph.rdfs:comment: A SpeakableSpecification indicates (typically via [[xpath]] or [[cssSelector]]) sections of a document that are highlighted as particularly [[speakable]]. Instances of this type are expected to be used primarily as values of the [[speakable]] property.

@graph.rdfs:label: Specialty
@graph.rdfs:comment: Any branch of a field in which people typically develop specific expertise, usually after significant study, time, and effort.

@graph.rdfs:label: SportingGoodsStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sporting goods store.

@graph.rdfs:label: SportsActivityLocation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sports location, such as a playing field.

@graph.rdfs:label: SportsClub
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sports club.

@graph.rdfs:label: SportsEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: Event type: Sports event.

@graph.rdfs:label: SportsOrganization
@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents the collection of all sports organizations, including sports teams, governing bodies, and sports associations.

@graph.rdfs:label: SportsTeam
@graph.rdfs:comment: Organization: Sports team.

@graph.rdfs:label: SpreadsheetDigitalDocument
@graph.rdfs:comment: A spreadsheet file.

@graph.rdfs:label: StadiumOrArena
@graph.rdfs:comment: A stadium.

@graph.rdfs:label: State
@graph.rdfs:comment: A state or province of a country.

@graph.rdfs:label: StatusEnumeration
@graph.rdfs:comment: Lists or enumerations dealing with status types.

@graph.rdfs:label: SteeringPositionValue
@graph.rdfs:comment: A value indicating a steering position.

@graph.rdfs:label: Store
@graph.rdfs:comment: A retail good store.

@graph.rdfs:label: StructuredValue
@graph.rdfs:comment: Structured values are used when the value of a property has a more complex structure than simply being a textual value or a reference to another thing.

@graph.rdfs:label: SubscribeAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of forming a personal connection with someone/something (object) unidirectionally/asymmetrically to get updates pushed to.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, SubscribeAction implies that the subscriber acts as a passive agent being constantly/actively pushed for updates.\\n* [[RegisterAction]]: Unlike RegisterAction, SubscribeAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.\\n* [[JoinAction]]: Unlike JoinAction, SubscribeAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.

@graph.rdfs:label: SubwayStation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A subway station.

@graph.rdfs:label: SuspendAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of momentarily pausing a device or application (e.g. pause music playback or pause a timer).

@graph.rdfs:label: Synagogue
@graph.rdfs:comment: A synagogue.

@graph.rdfs:label: TVClip
@graph.rdfs:comment: A short TV program or a segment/part of a TV program.

@graph.rdfs:label: TVEpisode
@graph.rdfs:comment: A TV episode which can be part of a series or season.

@graph.rdfs:label: TVSeason
@graph.rdfs:comment: Season dedicated to TV broadcast and associated online delivery.

@graph.rdfs:label: TVSeries
@graph.rdfs:comment: CreativeWorkSeries dedicated to TV broadcast and associated online delivery.

@graph.rdfs:label: Table
@graph.rdfs:comment: A table on a Web page.

@graph.rdfs:label: TakeAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of gaining ownership of an object from an origin. Reciprocal of GiveAction.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[GiveAction]]: The reciprocal of TakeAction.\\n* [[ReceiveAction]]: Unlike ReceiveAction, TakeAction implies that ownership has been transferred.

@graph.rdfs:label: TattooParlor
@graph.rdfs:comment: A tattoo parlor.

@graph.rdfs:label: Taxi
@graph.rdfs:comment: A taxi.

@graph.rdfs:label: TaxiReservation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A reservation for a taxi.\\n\\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

@graph.rdfs:label: TaxiService
@graph.rdfs:comment: A service for a vehicle for hire with a driver for local travel. Fares are usually calculated based on distance traveled.

@graph.rdfs:label: TaxiStand
@graph.rdfs:comment: A taxi stand.

@graph.rdfs:label: TechArticle
@graph.rdfs:comment: A technical article - Example: How-to (task) topics, step-by-step, procedural troubleshooting, specifications, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: TelevisionChannel
@graph.rdfs:comment: A unique instance of a television BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

@graph.rdfs:label: TelevisionStation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A television station.

@graph.rdfs:label: TennisComplex
@graph.rdfs:comment: A tennis complex.

@graph.rdfs:label: TextDigitalDocument
@graph.rdfs:comment: A file composed primarily of text.

@graph.rdfs:label: TextObject
@graph.rdfs:comment: A text file. The text can be unformatted or contain markup, html, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: TheaterEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: Event type: Theater performance.

@graph.rdfs:label: TheaterGroup
@graph.rdfs:comment: A theater group or company, for example, the Royal Shakespeare Company or Druid Theatre.

@graph.rdfs:label: Thing
@graph.rdfs:comment: The most generic type of item.

@graph.rdfs:label: Ticket
@graph.rdfs:comment: Used to describe a ticket to an event, a flight, a bus ride, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: TieAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of reaching a draw in a competitive activity.

@graph.rdfs:label: TipAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of giving money voluntarily to a beneficiary in recognition of services rendered.

@graph.rdfs:label: TireShop
@graph.rdfs:comment: A tire shop.

@graph.rdfs:label: TouristAttraction
@graph.rdfs:comment: A tourist attraction.  In principle any Thing can be a [[TouristAttraction]], from a [[Mountain]] and [[LandmarksOrHistoricalBuildings]] to a [[LocalBusiness]].  This Type can be used on its own to describe a general [[TouristAttraction]], or be used as an [[additionalType]] to add tourist attraction properties to any other type.  (See examples below)

@graph.rdfs:label: TouristInformationCenter
@graph.rdfs:comment: A tourist information center.

@graph.rdfs:label: ToyStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A toy store.

@graph.rdfs:label: TrackAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: An agent tracks an object for updates.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, TrackAction refers to the interest on the location of innanimates objects.\\n* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, TrackAction refers to  the interest on the location of innanimate objects.

@graph.rdfs:label: TradeAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of participating in an exchange of goods and services for monetary compensation. An agent trades an object, product or service with a participant in exchange for a one time or periodic payment.

@graph.rdfs:label: TrainReservation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A reservation for train travel.\\n\\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

@graph.rdfs:label: TrainStation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A train station.

@graph.rdfs:label: TrainTrip
@graph.rdfs:comment: A trip on a commercial train line.

@graph.rdfs:label: TransferAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of transferring/moving (abstract or concrete) animate or inanimate objects from one place to another.

@graph.rdfs:label: TravelAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of traveling from a fromLocation to a destination by a specified mode of transport, optionally with participants.

@graph.rdfs:label: TravelAgency
@graph.rdfs:comment: A travel agency.

@graph.rdfs:label: Trip
@graph.rdfs:comment: A trip or journey. An itinerary of visits to one or more places.

@graph.rdfs:label: TypeAndQuantityNode
@graph.rdfs:comment: A structured value indicating the quantity, unit of measurement, and business function of goods included in a bundle offer.

@graph.rdfs:label: URL
@graph.rdfs:comment: Data type: URL.

@graph.rdfs:label: UnRegisterAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of un-registering from a service.\\n\\nRelated actions:\\n\\n* [[RegisterAction]]: antonym of UnRegisterAction.\\n* [[LeaveAction]]: Unlike LeaveAction, UnRegisterAction implies that you are unregistering from a service you were previously registered, rather than leaving a team/group of people.

@graph.rdfs:label: UnitPriceSpecification
@graph.rdfs:comment: The price asked for a given offer by the respective organization or person.

@graph.rdfs:label: UpdateAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of managing by changing/editing the state of the object.

@graph.rdfs:label: UseAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of applying an object to its intended purpose.

@graph.rdfs:label: UserBlocks
@graph.rdfs:comment: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

@graph.rdfs:label: UserCheckins
