@graph.rdfs:comment: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

@graph.rdfs:label: UserLikes
@graph.rdfs:comment: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

@graph.rdfs:label: UserPageVisits
@graph.rdfs:comment: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

@graph.rdfs:label: UserPlays
@graph.rdfs:comment: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

@graph.rdfs:label: UserPlusOnes
@graph.rdfs:comment: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

@graph.rdfs:label: UserTweets
@graph.rdfs:comment: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

@graph.rdfs:label: VacationRental
@graph.rdfs:comment: A kind of lodging business that focuses on renting single properties for limited time.

@graph.rdfs:label: Vehicle
@graph.rdfs:comment: A vehicle is a device that is designed or used to transport people or cargo over land, water, air, or through space.

@graph.rdfs:label: VideoGallery
@graph.rdfs:comment: Web page type: Video gallery page.

@graph.rdfs:label: VideoGame
@graph.rdfs:comment: A video game is an electronic game that involves human interaction with a user interface to generate visual feedback on a video device.

@graph.rdfs:label: VideoGameClip
@graph.rdfs:comment: A short segment/part of a video game.

@graph.rdfs:label: VideoGameSeries
@graph.rdfs:comment: A video game series.

@graph.rdfs:label: VideoObject
@graph.rdfs:comment: A video file.

@graph.rdfs:label: ViewAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of consuming static visual content.

@graph.rdfs:label: VisualArtsEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: Event type: Visual arts event.

@graph.rdfs:label: VisualArtwork
@graph.rdfs:comment: A work of art that is primarily visual in character.

@graph.rdfs:label: Volcano
@graph.rdfs:comment: A volcano, like Fujisan.

@graph.rdfs:label: VoteAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of expressing a preference from a fixed/finite/structured set of choices/options.

@graph.rdfs:label: WPAdBlock
@graph.rdfs:comment: An advertising section of the page.

@graph.rdfs:label: WPFooter
@graph.rdfs:comment: The footer section of the page.

@graph.rdfs:label: WPHeader
@graph.rdfs:comment: The header section of the page.

@graph.rdfs:label: WPSideBar
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sidebar section of the page.

@graph.rdfs:label: WantAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of expressing a desire about the object. An agent wants an object.

@graph.rdfs:label: WarrantyPromise
@graph.rdfs:comment: A structured value representing the duration and scope of services that will be provided to a customer free of charge in case of a defect or malfunction of a product.

@graph.rdfs:label: WatchAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of consuming dynamic/moving visual content.

@graph.rdfs:label: Waterfall
@graph.rdfs:comment: A waterfall, like Niagara.

@graph.rdfs:label: WearAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of dressing oneself in clothing.

@graph.rdfs:label: WebApplication
@graph.rdfs:comment: Web applications.

@graph.rdfs:label: WebPage
@graph.rdfs:comment: A web page. Every web page is implicitly assumed to be declared to be of type WebPage, so the various properties about that webpage, such as breadcrumb may be used. We recommend explicit declaration if these properties are specified, but if they are found outside of an itemscope, they will be assumed to be about the page.

@graph.rdfs:label: WebPageElement
@graph.rdfs:comment: A web page element, like a table or an image.

@graph.rdfs:label: WebSite
@graph.rdfs:comment: A WebSite is a set of related web pages and other items typically served from a single web domain and accessible via URLs.

@graph.rdfs:label: WholesaleStore
@graph.rdfs:comment: A wholesale store.

@graph.rdfs:label: WinAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of achieving victory in a competitive activity.

@graph.rdfs:label: Winery
@graph.rdfs:comment: A winery.

@graph.rdfs:label: WorkersUnion
@graph.rdfs:comment: A Workers Union (also known as a Labor Union, Labour Union, or Trade Union) is an organization that promotes the interests of its worker members by collectively bargaining with management, organizing, and political lobbying.

@graph.rdfs:label: WriteAction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of authoring written creative content.

@graph.rdfs:label: Zoo
@graph.rdfs:comment: A zoo.

@graph.rdfs:label: acceptedAnswer
@graph.rdfs:comment: The answer(s) that has been accepted as best, typically on a Question/Answer site. Sites vary in their selection mechanisms, e.g. drawing on community opinion and/or the view of the Question author.

@graph.rdfs:label: acceptedOffer
@graph.rdfs:comment: The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.

@graph.rdfs:label: acceptedPaymentMethod
@graph.rdfs:comment: The payment method(s) that are accepted in general by an organization, or for some specific demand or offer.

@graph.rdfs:label: acceptsReservations
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be Boolean, an URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards compatibility) the strings ```Yes``` or ```No```.

@graph.rdfs:label: accessCode
@graph.rdfs:comment: Password, PIN, or access code needed for delivery (e.g. from a locker).

@graph.rdfs:label: accessMode
@graph.rdfs:comment: The human sensory perceptual system or cognitive faculty through which a person may process or perceive information. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessMode-vocabulary).

@graph.rdfs:label: accessModeSufficient
@graph.rdfs:comment: A list of single or combined accessModes that are sufficient to understand all the intellectual content of a resource. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessModeSufficient-vocabulary).

@graph.rdfs:label: accessibilityAPI
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityAPI-vocabulary).

@graph.rdfs:label: accessibilityControl
@graph.rdfs:comment: Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityControl-vocabulary).

@graph.rdfs:label: accessibilityFeature
@graph.rdfs:comment: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityFeature-vocabulary).

@graph.rdfs:label: accessibilityHazard
@graph.rdfs:comment: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityHazard-vocabulary).

@graph.rdfs:label: accessibilitySummary
@graph.rdfs:comment: A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as \

@graph.rdfs:label: accountId
@graph.rdfs:comment: The identifier for the account the payment will be applied to.

@graph.rdfs:label: accountablePerson
@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

@graph.rdfs:label: acquiredFrom
@graph.rdfs:comment: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

@graph.rdfs:label: actionAccessibilityRequirement
@graph.rdfs:comment: A set of requirements that must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action. If more than one value is specified, fulfilling one set of requirements will allow the Action to be performed.

@graph.rdfs:label: actionPlatform
@graph.rdfs:comment: The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.

@graph.rdfs:label: actionProcess
@graph.rdfs:comment: Description of the process by which the action was performed.

@graph.rdfs:label: actionStatus
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.

@graph.rdfs:label: actors
@graph.rdfs:comment: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

@graph.rdfs:label: addOn
@graph.rdfs:comment: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

@graph.rdfs:label: additionalName
@graph.rdfs:comment: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.

@graph.rdfs:label: additionalNumberOfGuests
@graph.rdfs:comment: If responding yes, the number of guests who will attend in addition to the invitee.

@graph.rdfs:label: address
@graph.rdfs:comment: Physical address of the item.

@graph.rdfs:label: addressLocality
@graph.rdfs:comment: The locality in which the street address is, and which is in the region. For example, Mountain View.

@graph.rdfs:label: addressRegion
@graph.rdfs:comment: The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level [Administrative division](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_administrative_divisions_by_country).

@graph.rdfs:label: advanceBookingRequirement
@graph.rdfs:comment: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

@graph.rdfs:label: affiliation
@graph.rdfs:comment: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.

@graph.rdfs:label: afterMedia
@graph.rdfs:comment: A media object representing the circumstances after performing this direction.

@graph.rdfs:label: agent
@graph.rdfs:comment: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). E.g. *John* wrote a book.

@graph.rdfs:label: aggregateRating
@graph.rdfs:comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

@graph.rdfs:label: aircraft
@graph.rdfs:comment: The kind of aircraft (e.g., \

@graph.rdfs:label: albumProductionType
@graph.rdfs:comment: Classification of the album by its type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: albumReleaseType
@graph.rdfs:comment: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

@graph.rdfs:label: albums
@graph.rdfs:comment: A collection of music albums.

@graph.rdfs:label: alignmentType
@graph.rdfs:comment: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', and 'educationalSubject'.

@graph.rdfs:label: alternativeHeadline
@graph.rdfs:comment: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

@graph.rdfs:label: amenityFeature
@graph.rdfs:comment: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

@graph.rdfs:label: amount
@graph.rdfs:comment: The amount of money.

@graph.rdfs:label: amountOfThisGood
@graph.rdfs:comment: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

@graph.rdfs:label: annualPercentageRate
@graph.rdfs:comment: The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.

@graph.rdfs:label: answerCount
@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of answers this question has received.

@graph.rdfs:label: application
@graph.rdfs:comment: An application that can complete the request.

@graph.rdfs:label: applicationCategory
@graph.rdfs:comment: Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.

@graph.rdfs:label: applicationSubCategory
@graph.rdfs:comment: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

@graph.rdfs:label: applicationSuite
@graph.rdfs:comment: The name of the application suite to which the application belongs (e.g. Excel belongs to Office).

@graph.rdfs:label: appliesToDeliveryMethod
@graph.rdfs:comment: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

@graph.rdfs:label: appliesToPaymentMethod
@graph.rdfs:comment: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.

@graph.rdfs:label: area
@graph.rdfs:comment: The area within which users can expect to reach the broadcast service.

@graph.rdfs:label: arrivalAirport
@graph.rdfs:comment: The airport where the flight terminates.

@graph.rdfs:label: arrivalBusStop
@graph.rdfs:comment: The stop or station from which the bus arrives.

@graph.rdfs:label: arrivalGate
@graph.rdfs:comment: Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.

@graph.rdfs:label: arrivalPlatform
@graph.rdfs:comment: The platform where the train arrives.

@graph.rdfs:label: arrivalStation
@graph.rdfs:comment: The station where the train trip ends.

@graph.rdfs:label: arrivalTerminal
@graph.rdfs:comment: Identifier of the flight's arrival terminal.

@graph.rdfs:label: arrivalTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The expected arrival time.

@graph.rdfs:label: artEdition
@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example \

@graph.rdfs:label: artMedium
@graph.rdfs:comment: The material used. (E.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)

@graph.rdfs:label: artform
@graph.rdfs:comment: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: articleBody
@graph.rdfs:comment: The actual body of the article.

@graph.rdfs:label: articleSection
@graph.rdfs:comment: Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: assembly
@graph.rdfs:comment: Library file name, e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

@graph.rdfs:label: assemblyVersion
@graph.rdfs:comment: Associated product/technology version. E.g., .NET Framework 4.5.

@graph.rdfs:label: associatedArticle
@graph.rdfs:comment: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.

@graph.rdfs:label: associatedMedia
@graph.rdfs:comment: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

@graph.rdfs:label: athlete
@graph.rdfs:comment: A person that acts as performing member of a sports team; a player as opposed to a coach.

@graph.rdfs:label: attendees
@graph.rdfs:comment: A person attending the event.

@graph.rdfs:label: audienceType
@graph.rdfs:comment: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).

@graph.rdfs:label: audio
@graph.rdfs:comment: An embedded audio object.

@graph.rdfs:label: authenticator
@graph.rdfs:comment: The Organization responsible for authenticating the user's subscription. For example, many media apps require a cable/satellite provider to authenticate your subscription before playing media.

@graph.rdfs:label: author
@graph.rdfs:comment: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

@graph.rdfs:label: availability
@graph.rdfs:comment: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: availabilityEnds
@graph.rdfs:comment: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

@graph.rdfs:label: availabilityStarts
@graph.rdfs:comment: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

@graph.rdfs:label: availableAtOrFrom
@graph.rdfs:comment: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

@graph.rdfs:label: availableChannel
@graph.rdfs:comment: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

@graph.rdfs:label: availableDeliveryMethod
@graph.rdfs:comment: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

@graph.rdfs:label: availableFrom
@graph.rdfs:comment: When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: availableLanguage
@graph.rdfs:comment: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[inLanguage]].

@graph.rdfs:label: availableThrough
@graph.rdfs:comment: After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.

@graph.rdfs:label: awards
@graph.rdfs:comment: Awards won by or for this item.

@graph.rdfs:label: awayTeam
@graph.rdfs:comment: The away team in a sports event.

@graph.rdfs:label: baseSalary
@graph.rdfs:comment: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

@graph.rdfs:label: bccRecipient
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of recipient. The recipient blind copied on a message.

@graph.rdfs:label: beforeMedia
@graph.rdfs:comment: A media object representing the circumstances before performing this direction.

@graph.rdfs:label: benefits
@graph.rdfs:comment: Description of benefits associated with the job.

@graph.rdfs:label: bestRating
@graph.rdfs:comment: The highest value allowed in this rating system.

@graph.rdfs:label: billingAddress
@graph.rdfs:comment: The billing address for the order.

@graph.rdfs:label: billingIncrement
@graph.rdfs:comment: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

@graph.rdfs:label: billingPeriod
@graph.rdfs:comment: The time interval used to compute the invoice.

@graph.rdfs:label: birthDate
@graph.rdfs:comment: Date of birth.

@graph.rdfs:label: birthPlace
@graph.rdfs:comment: The place where the person was born.

@graph.rdfs:label: bitrate
@graph.rdfs:comment: The bitrate of the media object.

@graph.rdfs:label: blogPosts
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates a post that is part of a [[Blog]]. Note that historically, what we term a \

@graph.rdfs:label: boardingGroup
@graph.rdfs:comment: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.

@graph.rdfs:label: boardingPolicy
@graph.rdfs:comment: The type of boarding policy used by the airline (e.g. zone-based or group-based).

@graph.rdfs:label: bookEdition
@graph.rdfs:comment: The edition of the book.

@graph.rdfs:label: bookFormat
@graph.rdfs:comment: The format of the book.

@graph.rdfs:label: bookingAgent
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.

@graph.rdfs:label: bookingTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date and time the reservation was booked.

@graph.rdfs:label: borrower
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.

@graph.rdfs:label: box
@graph.rdfs:comment: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

@graph.rdfs:label: branchOf
@graph.rdfs:comment: The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any. Not to be confused with (anatomical) [[branch]].

@graph.rdfs:label: brand
@graph.rdfs:comment: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

@graph.rdfs:label: breadcrumb
@graph.rdfs:comment: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

@graph.rdfs:label: broadcastAffiliateOf
@graph.rdfs:comment: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.

@graph.rdfs:label: broadcastChannelId
@graph.rdfs:comment: The unique address by which the BroadcastService can be identified in a provider lineup. In US, this is typically a number.

@graph.rdfs:label: broadcastDisplayName
@graph.rdfs:comment: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.

@graph.rdfs:label: broadcastFrequency
@graph.rdfs:comment: The frequency used for over-the-air broadcasts. Numeric values or simple ranges, e.g. 87-99. In addition a shortcut idiom is supported for frequencies of AM and FM radio channels, e.g. \

@graph.rdfs:label: broadcastFrequencyValue
@graph.rdfs:comment: The frequency in MHz for a particular broadcast.

@graph.rdfs:label: broadcastOfEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.

@graph.rdfs:label: broadcastServiceTier
@graph.rdfs:comment: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).

@graph.rdfs:label: broadcastTimezone
@graph.rdfs:comment: The timezone in [ISO 8601 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) for which the service bases its broadcasts.

@graph.rdfs:label: broadcaster
@graph.rdfs:comment: The organization owning or operating the broadcast service.

@graph.rdfs:label: browserRequirements
@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.

@graph.rdfs:label: busName
@graph.rdfs:comment: The name of the bus (e.g. Bolt Express).

@graph.rdfs:label: busNumber
@graph.rdfs:comment: The unique identifier for the bus.

@graph.rdfs:label: businessDays
@graph.rdfs:comment: Days of the week when the merchant typically operates, indicated via opening hours markup.

@graph.rdfs:label: businessFunction
@graph.rdfs:comment: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

@graph.rdfs:label: buyer
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of participant. The participant/person/organization that bought the object.

@graph.rdfs:label: byArtist
@graph.rdfs:comment: The artist that performed this album or recording.

@graph.rdfs:label: calories
@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of calories.

@graph.rdfs:label: candidate
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of object. The candidate subject of this action.

@graph.rdfs:label: caption
@graph.rdfs:comment: The caption for this object. For downloadable machine formats (closed caption, subtitles etc.) use MediaObject and indicate the [[encodingFormat]].

@graph.rdfs:label: carbohydrateContent
@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of grams of carbohydrates.

@graph.rdfs:label: cargoVolume
@graph.rdfs:comment: The available volume for cargo or luggage. For automobiles, this is usually the trunk volume.\\n\\nTypical unit code(s): LTR for liters, FTQ for cubic foot/feet\\n\\nNote: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

@graph.rdfs:label: carrier
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'carrier' is an out-dated term indicating the 'provider' for parcel delivery and flights.

@graph.rdfs:label: carrierRequirements
@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies specific carrier(s) requirements for the application (e.g. an application may only work on a specific carrier network).

@graph.rdfs:label: catalog
@graph.rdfs:comment: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

@graph.rdfs:label: catalogNumber
@graph.rdfs:comment: The catalog number for the release.

@graph.rdfs:label: category
@graph.rdfs:comment: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

@graph.rdfs:label: ccRecipient
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of recipient. The recipient copied on a message.

@graph.rdfs:label: character
@graph.rdfs:comment: Fictional person connected with a creative work.

@graph.rdfs:label: characterAttribute
@graph.rdfs:comment: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

@graph.rdfs:label: characterName
@graph.rdfs:comment: The name of a character played in some acting or performing role, i.e. in a PerformanceRole.

@graph.rdfs:label: cheatCode
@graph.rdfs:comment: Cheat codes to the game.

@graph.rdfs:label: checkinTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

@graph.rdfs:label: checkoutTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.

@graph.rdfs:label: childMaxAge
@graph.rdfs:comment: Maximal age of the child.

@graph.rdfs:label: childMinAge
@graph.rdfs:comment: Minimal age of the child.

@graph.rdfs:label: children
@graph.rdfs:comment: A child of the person.

@graph.rdfs:label: cholesterolContent
@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of milligrams of cholesterol.

@graph.rdfs:label: circle
@graph.rdfs:comment: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.

@graph.rdfs:label: citation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: claimReviewed
@graph.rdfs:comment: A short summary of the specific claims reviewed in a ClaimReview.

@graph.rdfs:label: clipNumber
@graph.rdfs:comment: Position of the clip within an ordered group of clips.

@graph.rdfs:label: closes
@graph.rdfs:comment: The closing hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

@graph.rdfs:label: coach
@graph.rdfs:comment: A person that acts in a coaching role for a sports team.

@graph.rdfs:label: codeRepository
@graph.rdfs:comment: Link to the repository where the un-compiled, human readable code and related code is located (SVN, GitHub, CodePlex).

@graph.rdfs:label: colleagues
@graph.rdfs:comment: A colleague of the person.

@graph.rdfs:label: collection
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

@graph.rdfs:label: color
@graph.rdfs:comment: The color of the product.

@graph.rdfs:label: comment
@graph.rdfs:comment: Comments, typically from users.

@graph.rdfs:label: commentCount
@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

@graph.rdfs:label: commentText
@graph.rdfs:comment: The text of the UserComment.

@graph.rdfs:label: commentTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The time at which the UserComment was made.

@graph.rdfs:label: composer
@graph.rdfs:comment: The person or organization who wrote a composition, or who is the composer of a work performed at some event.

@graph.rdfs:label: confirmationNumber
@graph.rdfs:comment: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

@graph.rdfs:label: contactOption
@graph.rdfs:comment: An option available on this contact point (e.g. a toll-free number or support for hearing-impaired callers).

@graph.rdfs:label: contactPoints
@graph.rdfs:comment: A contact point for a person or organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: contactType
@graph.rdfs:comment: A person or organization can have different contact points, for different purposes. For example, a sales contact point, a PR contact point and so on. This property is used to specify the kind of contact point.

@graph.rdfs:label: containedIn
@graph.rdfs:comment: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

@graph.rdfs:label: contentRating
@graph.rdfs:comment: Official rating of a piece of content—for example, 'MPAA PG-13'.

@graph.rdfs:label: contentSize
@graph.rdfs:comment: File size in (mega/kilo)bytes.

@graph.rdfs:label: contentType
@graph.rdfs:comment: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

@graph.rdfs:label: contentUrl
@graph.rdfs:comment: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

@graph.rdfs:label: contributor
@graph.rdfs:comment: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork or Event.

@graph.rdfs:label: cookTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The time it takes to actually cook the dish, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

@graph.rdfs:label: cookingMethod
@graph.rdfs:comment: The method of cooking, such as Frying, Steaming, ...

@graph.rdfs:label: copyrightHolder
@graph.rdfs:comment: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

@graph.rdfs:label: copyrightYear
@graph.rdfs:comment: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

@graph.rdfs:label: countriesNotSupported
@graph.rdfs:comment: Countries for which the application is not supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

@graph.rdfs:label: countriesSupported
@graph.rdfs:comment: Countries for which the application is supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

@graph.rdfs:label: course
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

@graph.rdfs:label: courseCode
@graph.rdfs:comment: The identifier for the [[Course]] used by the course [[provider]] (e.g. CS101 or 6.001).

@graph.rdfs:label: courseMode
@graph.rdfs:comment: The medium or means of delivery of the course instance or the mode of study, either as a text label (e.g. \

@graph.rdfs:label: coursePrerequisites
@graph.rdfs:comment: Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another [[Course]] or a textual description like \

@graph.rdfs:label: coverageEndTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.

@graph.rdfs:label: coverageStartTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.

@graph.rdfs:label: creator
@graph.rdfs:comment: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

@graph.rdfs:label: creditedTo
@graph.rdfs:comment: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to \

@graph.rdfs:label: cssSelector
@graph.rdfs:comment: A CSS selector, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual \

@graph.rdfs:label: currenciesAccepted
@graph.rdfs:comment: The currency accepted.\\n\\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. \

@graph.rdfs:label: currency
@graph.rdfs:comment: The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.\\n\\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. \

@graph.rdfs:label: customer
@graph.rdfs:comment: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

@graph.rdfs:label: cutoffTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: Order cutoff time allows merchants to describe the time after which they will no longer process orders received on that day. For orders processed after cutoff time, one day gets added to the delivery time estimate. This property is expected to be most typically used via the [[ShippingRateSettings]] publication pattern. The time is indicated using the ISO-8601 Time format, e.g. \

@graph.rdfs:label: dataFeedElement
@graph.rdfs:comment: An item within a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

@graph.rdfs:label: datasetTimeInterval
@graph.rdfs:comment: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

@graph.rdfs:label: dateCreated
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

@graph.rdfs:label: dateDeleted
@graph.rdfs:comment: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

@graph.rdfs:label: dateIssued
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date the ticket was issued.

@graph.rdfs:label: dateModified
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

@graph.rdfs:label: datePosted
@graph.rdfs:comment: Publication date of an online listing.

@graph.rdfs:label: datePublished
@graph.rdfs:comment: Date of first publication or broadcast. For example the date a [[CreativeWork]] was broadcast or a [[Certification]] was issued.

@graph.rdfs:label: dateRead
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.

@graph.rdfs:label: dateReceived
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date/time the message was received if a single recipient exists.

@graph.rdfs:label: dateSent
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date/time at which the message was sent.

@graph.rdfs:label: dateVehicleFirstRegistered
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

@graph.rdfs:label: dayOfWeek
@graph.rdfs:comment: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

@graph.rdfs:label: deathDate
@graph.rdfs:comment: Date of death.

@graph.rdfs:label: deathPlace
@graph.rdfs:comment: The place where the person died.

@graph.rdfs:label: defaultValue
@graph.rdfs:comment: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

@graph.rdfs:label: deliveryAddress
@graph.rdfs:comment: Destination address.

@graph.rdfs:label: deliveryLeadTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

@graph.rdfs:label: deliveryMethod
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

@graph.rdfs:label: deliveryStatus
@graph.rdfs:comment: New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).

@graph.rdfs:label: deliveryTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The total delay between the receipt of the order and the goods reaching the final customer.

@graph.rdfs:label: department
@graph.rdfs:comment: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

@graph.rdfs:label: departureAirport
@graph.rdfs:comment: The airport where the flight originates.

@graph.rdfs:label: departureBusStop
@graph.rdfs:comment: The stop or station from which the bus departs.

@graph.rdfs:label: departureGate
@graph.rdfs:comment: Identifier of the flight's departure gate.

@graph.rdfs:label: departurePlatform
@graph.rdfs:comment: The platform from which the train departs.

@graph.rdfs:label: departureStation
@graph.rdfs:comment: The station from which the train departs.

@graph.rdfs:label: departureTerminal
@graph.rdfs:comment: Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.

@graph.rdfs:label: departureTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The expected departure time.

@graph.rdfs:label: dependencies
@graph.rdfs:comment: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

@graph.rdfs:label: depth
@graph.rdfs:comment: The depth of the item.

@graph.rdfs:label: device
@graph.rdfs:comment: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

@graph.rdfs:label: directors
@graph.rdfs:comment: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

@graph.rdfs:label: disambiguatingDescription
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

@graph.rdfs:label: discount
@graph.rdfs:comment: Any discount applied (to an Order).

@graph.rdfs:label: discountCode
@graph.rdfs:comment: Code used to redeem a discount.

@graph.rdfs:label: discountCurrency
@graph.rdfs:comment: The currency of the discount.\\n\\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. \

@graph.rdfs:label: discusses
@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies the CreativeWork associated with the UserComment.

@graph.rdfs:label: discussionUrl
@graph.rdfs:comment: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

@graph.rdfs:label: dissolutionDate
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date that this organization was dissolved.

@graph.rdfs:label: distance
@graph.rdfs:comment: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

@graph.rdfs:label: distribution
@graph.rdfs:comment: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format. This property can be repeated if different variations are available. There is no expectation that different downloadable distributions must contain exactly equivalent information (see also [DCAT](https://www.w3.org/TR/vocab-dcat-3/#Class:Distribution) on this point). Different distributions might include or exclude different subsets of the entire dataset, for example.

@graph.rdfs:label: doesNotShip
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates when shipping to a particular [[shippingDestination]] is not available.

@graph.rdfs:label: doorTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The time admission will commence.

@graph.rdfs:label: downloadUrl
@graph.rdfs:comment: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

@graph.rdfs:label: downvoteCount
@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

@graph.rdfs:label: driveWheelConfiguration
@graph.rdfs:comment: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

@graph.rdfs:label: dropoffLocation
@graph.rdfs:comment: Where a rental car can be dropped off.

@graph.rdfs:label: dropoffTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: When a rental car can be dropped off.

@graph.rdfs:label: duns
@graph.rdfs:comment: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

@graph.rdfs:label: durationOfWarranty
@graph.rdfs:comment: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

@graph.rdfs:label: duringMedia
@graph.rdfs:comment: A media object representing the circumstances while performing this direction.

@graph.rdfs:label: editor
@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

@graph.rdfs:label: educationRequirements
@graph.rdfs:comment: Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

@graph.rdfs:label: educationalFramework
@graph.rdfs:comment: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

@graph.rdfs:label: educationalRole
@graph.rdfs:comment: An educationalRole of an EducationalAudience.

@graph.rdfs:label: educationalUse
@graph.rdfs:comment: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

@graph.rdfs:label: elevation
@graph.rdfs:comment: The elevation of a location ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)). Values may be of the form 'NUMBER UNIT\\_OF\\_MEASUREMENT' (e.g., '1,000 m', '3,200 ft') while numbers alone should be assumed to be a value in meters.

@graph.rdfs:label: eligibleCustomerType
@graph.rdfs:comment: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

@graph.rdfs:label: eligibleDuration
@graph.rdfs:comment: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

@graph.rdfs:label: eligibleQuantity
@graph.rdfs:comment: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

@graph.rdfs:label: eligibleTransactionVolume
@graph.rdfs:comment: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

@graph.rdfs:label: email
@graph.rdfs:comment: Email address.

@graph.rdfs:label: embedUrl
@graph.rdfs:comment: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the ```src``` element of an ```embed``` tag and should not be the same as the content of the ```loc``` tag.

@graph.rdfs:label: employees
@graph.rdfs:comment: People working for this organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: employmentType
@graph.rdfs:comment: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).

@graph.rdfs:label: encodingType
@graph.rdfs:comment: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.

@graph.rdfs:label: encodings
@graph.rdfs:comment: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork.

@graph.rdfs:label: endDate
@graph.rdfs:comment: The end date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

@graph.rdfs:label: endTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the end of a clip within a larger file.\\n\\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

@graph.rdfs:label: endorsee
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

@graph.rdfs:label: entertainmentBusiness
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.

@graph.rdfs:label: episodeNumber
@graph.rdfs:comment: Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.

@graph.rdfs:label: episodes
@graph.rdfs:comment: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

@graph.rdfs:label: equal
@graph.rdfs:comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

@graph.rdfs:label: error
@graph.rdfs:comment: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure.

@graph.rdfs:label: estimatedCost
@graph.rdfs:comment: The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.

@graph.rdfs:label: estimatedFlightDuration
@graph.rdfs:comment: The estimated time the flight will take.

@graph.rdfs:label: estimatedSalary
@graph.rdfs:comment: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

@graph.rdfs:label: eventStatus
@graph.rdfs:comment: An eventStatus of an event represents its status; particularly useful when an event is cancelled or rescheduled.

@graph.rdfs:label: events
@graph.rdfs:comment: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: exifData
@graph.rdfs:comment: exif data for this object.

@graph.rdfs:label: expectedArrivalFrom
@graph.rdfs:comment: The earliest date the package may arrive.

@graph.rdfs:label: expectedArrivalUntil
@graph.rdfs:comment: The latest date the package may arrive.

@graph.rdfs:label: expectsAcceptanceOf
@graph.rdfs:comment: An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.

@graph.rdfs:label: experienceRequirements
@graph.rdfs:comment: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

@graph.rdfs:label: expires
@graph.rdfs:comment: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a [[VideoObject]] or [[NewsArticle]] whose availability or relevance is time-limited, a [[ClaimReview]] fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date, or a [[Certification]] the validity has expired.

@graph.rdfs:label: extendedAddress
@graph.rdfs:comment: An address extension such as an apartment number, C/O or alternative name.

@graph.rdfs:label: familyName
@graph.rdfs:comment: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of a Person.

@graph.rdfs:label: fatContent
@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of grams of fat.

@graph.rdfs:label: faxNumber
@graph.rdfs:comment: The fax number.

@graph.rdfs:label: featureList
@graph.rdfs:comment: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).

@graph.rdfs:label: feesAndCommissionsSpecification
@graph.rdfs:comment: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: fiberContent
@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of grams of fiber.

@graph.rdfs:label: fileFormat
@graph.rdfs:comment: Media type, typically MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml)) of the content, e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information. Unregistered or niche file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia entry.

@graph.rdfs:label: fileSize
@graph.rdfs:comment: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.

@graph.rdfs:label: firstPerformance
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date and place the work was first performed.

@graph.rdfs:label: flightDistance
@graph.rdfs:comment: The distance of the flight.

@graph.rdfs:label: flightNumber
@graph.rdfs:comment: The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.

@graph.rdfs:label: followee
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of object. The person or organization being followed.

@graph.rdfs:label: follows
@graph.rdfs:comment: The most generic uni-directional social relation.

@graph.rdfs:label: foodEstablishment
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.

@graph.rdfs:label: foodEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

@graph.rdfs:label: founders
@graph.rdfs:comment: A person who founded this organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: foundingDate
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date that this organization was founded.

@graph.rdfs:label: foundingLocation
@graph.rdfs:comment: The place where the Organization was founded.

@graph.rdfs:label: free
@graph.rdfs:comment: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

@graph.rdfs:label: freeShippingThreshold
@graph.rdfs:comment: A monetary value above (or at) which the shipping rate becomes free. Intended to be used via an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with [[shippingSettingsLink]] matching this [[ShippingRateSettings]].

@graph.rdfs:label: fromLocation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

@graph.rdfs:label: fuelConsumption
@graph.rdfs:comment: The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).\\n\\n* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km.  Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.\\n* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.\\n* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed (\

@graph.rdfs:label: fuelEfficiency
@graph.rdfs:comment: The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).\\n\\n* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.\\n* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.\\n* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed (\

@graph.rdfs:label: fuelType
@graph.rdfs:comment: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.

@graph.rdfs:label: funder
@graph.rdfs:comment: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

@graph.rdfs:label: gameEdition
@graph.rdfs:comment: The edition of a video game.

@graph.rdfs:label: gameItem
@graph.rdfs:comment: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

@graph.rdfs:label: gameLocation
@graph.rdfs:comment: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

@graph.rdfs:label: gamePlatform
@graph.rdfs:comment: The electronic systems used to play <a href=\

@graph.rdfs:label: gameTip
@graph.rdfs:comment: Links to tips, tactics, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: gender
@graph.rdfs:comment: Gender of something, typically a [[Person]], but possibly also fictional characters, animals, etc. While https://schema.org/Male and https://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who do not identify as a binary gender. The [[gender]] property can also be used in an extended sense to cover e.g. the gender of sports teams. As with the gender of individuals, we do not try to enumerate all possibilities. A mixed-gender [[SportsTeam]] can be indicated with a text value of \

@graph.rdfs:label: genre
@graph.rdfs:comment: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

@graph.rdfs:label: geo
@graph.rdfs:comment: The geo coordinates of the place.

@graph.rdfs:label: geoMidpoint
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape, e.g. GeoCircle.

@graph.rdfs:label: geoRadius
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

@graph.rdfs:label: geographicArea
@graph.rdfs:comment: The geographic area associated with the audience.

@graph.rdfs:label: givenName
@graph.rdfs:comment: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person.

@graph.rdfs:label: globalLocationNumber
@graph.rdfs:comment: The [Global Location Number](http://www.gs1.org/gln) (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

@graph.rdfs:label: grantee
@graph.rdfs:comment: The person, organization, contact point, or audience that has been granted this permission.

@graph.rdfs:label: greater
@graph.rdfs:comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.

@graph.rdfs:label: greaterOrEqual
@graph.rdfs:comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.

@graph.rdfs:label: gtin12
@graph.rdfs:comment: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

@graph.rdfs:label: gtin13
@graph.rdfs:comment: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceding zero. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

@graph.rdfs:label: gtin14
@graph.rdfs:comment: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

@graph.rdfs:label: gtin8
@graph.rdfs:comment: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

@graph.rdfs:label: hasCourseInstance
@graph.rdfs:comment: An offering of the course at a specific time and place or through specific media or mode of study or to a specific section of students.

@graph.rdfs:label: hasDeliveryMethod
@graph.rdfs:comment: Method used for delivery or shipping.

@graph.rdfs:label: hasDigitalDocumentPermission
@graph.rdfs:comment: A permission related to the access to this document (e.g. permission to read or write an electronic document). For a public document, specify a grantee with an Audience with audienceType equal to \

@graph.rdfs:label: hasMenuItem
@graph.rdfs:comment: A food or drink item contained in a menu or menu section.

@graph.rdfs:label: hasMenuSection
@graph.rdfs:comment: A subgrouping of the menu (by dishes, course, serving time period, etc.).

@graph.rdfs:label: hasOccupation
@graph.rdfs:comment: The Person's occupation. For past professions, use Role for expressing dates.

@graph.rdfs:label: hasOfferCatalog
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

@graph.rdfs:label: hasPOS
@graph.rdfs:comment: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

@graph.rdfs:label: headline
@graph.rdfs:comment: Headline of the article.

@graph.rdfs:label: height
@graph.rdfs:comment: The height of the item.

@graph.rdfs:label: highPrice
@graph.rdfs:comment: The highest price of all offers available.\\n\\nUsage guidelines:\\n\\n* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.\\n* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

@graph.rdfs:label: hiringOrganization
@graph.rdfs:comment: Organization or Person offering the job position.

@graph.rdfs:label: homeLocation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A contact location for a person's residence.

@graph.rdfs:label: homeTeam
@graph.rdfs:comment: The home team in a sports event.

@graph.rdfs:label: honorificPrefix
@graph.rdfs:comment: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

@graph.rdfs:label: honorificSuffix
@graph.rdfs:comment: An honorific suffix following a Person's name such as M.D./PhD/MSCSW.

@graph.rdfs:label: hostingOrganization
@graph.rdfs:comment: The Organization (airline, travelers' club, retailer, etc.) the membership is made with or which offers the  MemberProgram.

@graph.rdfs:label: hoursAvailable
@graph.rdfs:comment: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

@graph.rdfs:label: httpMethod
@graph.rdfs:comment: An HTTP method that specifies the appropriate HTTP method for a request to an HTTP EntryPoint. Values are capitalized strings as used in HTTP.

@graph.rdfs:label: iataCode
@graph.rdfs:comment: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

@graph.rdfs:label: icaoCode
@graph.rdfs:comment: ICAO identifier for an airport.

@graph.rdfs:label: illustrator
@graph.rdfs:comment: The illustrator of the book.

@graph.rdfs:label: inAlbum
@graph.rdfs:comment: The album to which this recording belongs.

@graph.rdfs:label: inBroadcastLineup
@graph.rdfs:comment: The CableOrSatelliteService offering the channel.

@graph.rdfs:label: inPlaylist
@graph.rdfs:comment: The playlist to which this recording belongs.

@graph.rdfs:label: incentives
@graph.rdfs:comment: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

@graph.rdfs:label: includedComposition
@graph.rdfs:comment: Smaller compositions included in this work (e.g. a movement in a symphony).

@graph.rdfs:label: includedDataCatalog
@graph.rdfs:comment: A data catalog which contains this dataset (this property was previously 'catalog', preferred name is now 'includedInDataCatalog').

@graph.rdfs:label: includesObject
@graph.rdfs:comment: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in  an [[Offer]] or [[ProductCollection]].

@graph.rdfs:label: industry
@graph.rdfs:comment: The industry associated with the job position.

@graph.rdfs:label: ingredients
@graph.rdfs:comment: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.
