@graph.rdfs:label: validThrough
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

@graph.rdfs:label: validUntil
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date when the item is no longer valid.

@graph.rdfs:label: value
@graph.rdfs:comment: The value of a [[QuantitativeValue]] (including [[Observation]]) or property value node.\\n\\n* For [[QuantitativeValue]] and [[MonetaryAmount]], the recommended type for values is 'Number'.\\n* For [[PropertyValue]], it can be 'Text', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.\\n* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.\\n* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

@graph.rdfs:label: valueAddedTaxIncluded
@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies whether the applicable value-added tax (VAT) is included in the price specification or not.

@graph.rdfs:label: valueMaxLength
@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

@graph.rdfs:label: valueMinLength
@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

@graph.rdfs:label: valueName
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates the name of the PropertyValueSpecification to be used in URL templates and form encoding in a manner analogous to HTML's input@name.

@graph.rdfs:label: valuePattern
@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

@graph.rdfs:label: valueReference
@graph.rdfs:comment: A secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature or a type of measurement.

@graph.rdfs:label: valueRequired
@graph.rdfs:comment: Whether the property must be filled in to complete the action.  Default is false.

@graph.rdfs:label: vatID
@graph.rdfs:comment: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

@graph.rdfs:label: vehicleConfiguration
@graph.rdfs:comment: A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

@graph.rdfs:label: vehicleEngine
@graph.rdfs:comment: Information about the engine or engines of the vehicle.

@graph.rdfs:label: vehicleIdentificationNumber
@graph.rdfs:comment: The Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) is a unique serial number used by the automotive industry to identify individual motor vehicles.

@graph.rdfs:label: vehicleInteriorColor
@graph.rdfs:comment: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

@graph.rdfs:label: vehicleInteriorType
@graph.rdfs:comment: The type or material of the interior of the vehicle (e.g. synthetic fabric, leather, wood, etc.). While most interior types are characterized by the material used, an interior type can also be based on vehicle usage or target audience.

@graph.rdfs:label: vehicleModelDate
@graph.rdfs:comment: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

@graph.rdfs:label: vehicleSeatingCapacity
@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of passengers that can be seated in the vehicle, both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\\n\\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

@graph.rdfs:label: vehicleSpecialUsage
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates whether the vehicle has been used for special purposes, like commercial rental, driving school, or as a taxi. The legislation in many countries requires this information to be revealed when offering a car for sale.

@graph.rdfs:label: vehicleTransmission
@graph.rdfs:comment: The type of component used for transmitting the power from a rotating power source to the wheels or other relevant component(s) (\

@graph.rdfs:label: vendor
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'vendor' is an earlier term for 'seller'.

@graph.rdfs:label: version
@graph.rdfs:comment: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

@graph.rdfs:label: video
@graph.rdfs:comment: An embedded video object.

@graph.rdfs:label: videoFormat
@graph.rdfs:comment: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

@graph.rdfs:label: videoFrameSize
@graph.rdfs:comment: The frame size of the video.

@graph.rdfs:label: videoQuality
@graph.rdfs:comment: The quality of the video.

@graph.rdfs:label: volumeNumber
@graph.rdfs:comment: Identifies the volume of publication or multi-part work; for example, \

@graph.rdfs:label: warrantyPromise
@graph.rdfs:comment: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

@graph.rdfs:label: warrantyScope
@graph.rdfs:comment: The scope of the warranty promise.

@graph.rdfs:label: webCheckinTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The time when a passenger can check into the flight online.

@graph.rdfs:label: weight
@graph.rdfs:comment: The weight of the product or person.

@graph.rdfs:label: width
@graph.rdfs:comment: The width of the item.

@graph.rdfs:label: winner
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of participant. The winner of the action.

@graph.rdfs:label: wordCount
@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of words in the text of the CreativeWork such as an Article, Book, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: workHours
@graph.rdfs:comment: The typical working hours for this job (e.g. 1st shift, night shift, 8am-5pm).

@graph.rdfs:label: workLocation
@graph.rdfs:comment: A contact location for a person's place of work.

@graph.rdfs:label: workPerformed
@graph.rdfs:comment: A work performed in some event, for example a play performed in a TheaterEvent.

@graph.rdfs:label: workPresented
@graph.rdfs:comment: The movie presented during this event.

@graph.rdfs:label: worksFor
@graph.rdfs:comment: Organizations that the person works for.

@graph.rdfs:label: worstRating
@graph.rdfs:comment: The lowest value allowed in this rating system.

@graph.rdfs:label: xpath
@graph.rdfs:comment: An XPath, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual \

@graph.rdfs:label: yearlyRevenue
@graph.rdfs:comment: The size of the business in annual revenue.

@graph.rdfs:label: yearsInOperation
@graph.rdfs:comment: The age of the business.

@graph.rdfs:label: actionApplication
@graph.rdfs:comment: An application that can complete the request.

@graph.rdfs:label: actionOption
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

@graph.rdfs:label: actor
@graph.rdfs:comment: An actor (individual or a group), e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

@graph.rdfs:label: album
@graph.rdfs:comment: A music album.

@graph.rdfs:label: albumRelease
@graph.rdfs:comment: A release of this album.

@graph.rdfs:label: alternateName
@graph.rdfs:comment: An alias for the item.

@graph.rdfs:label: alumni
@graph.rdfs:comment: Alumni of an organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: alumniOf
@graph.rdfs:comment: An organization that the person is an alumni of.

@graph.rdfs:label: artworkSurface
@graph.rdfs:comment: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: attendee
@graph.rdfs:comment: A person or organization attending the event.

@graph.rdfs:label: audience
@graph.rdfs:comment: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

@graph.rdfs:label: availableOnDevice
@graph.rdfs:comment: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

@graph.rdfs:label: award
@graph.rdfs:comment: An award won by or for this item.

@graph.rdfs:label: blogPost
@graph.rdfs:comment: A posting that is part of this blog.

@graph.rdfs:label: broker
@graph.rdfs:comment: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

@graph.rdfs:label: codeSampleType
@graph.rdfs:comment: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

@graph.rdfs:label: colleague
@graph.rdfs:comment: A colleague of the person.

@graph.rdfs:label: contactPoint
@graph.rdfs:comment: A contact point for a person or organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: containsPlace
@graph.rdfs:comment: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

@graph.rdfs:label: containsSeason
@graph.rdfs:comment: A season that is part of the media series.

@graph.rdfs:label: contentLocation
@graph.rdfs:comment: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

@graph.rdfs:label: dataset
@graph.rdfs:comment: A dataset contained in this catalog.

@graph.rdfs:label: description
@graph.rdfs:comment: A description of the item.

@graph.rdfs:label: director
@graph.rdfs:comment: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

@graph.rdfs:label: duration
@graph.rdfs:comment: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

@graph.rdfs:label: employee
@graph.rdfs:comment: Someone working for this organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: encodesCreativeWork
@graph.rdfs:comment: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

@graph.rdfs:label: episode
@graph.rdfs:comment: An episode of a TV, radio or game media within a series or season.

@graph.rdfs:label: event
@graph.rdfs:comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

@graph.rdfs:label: exampleOfWork
@graph.rdfs:comment: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.

@graph.rdfs:label: executableLibraryName
@graph.rdfs:comment: Library file name, e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

@graph.rdfs:label: exerciseCourse
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

@graph.rdfs:label: founder
@graph.rdfs:comment: A person or organization who founded this organization.

@graph.rdfs:label: game
@graph.rdfs:comment: Video game which is played on this server.

@graph.rdfs:label: gameServer
@graph.rdfs:comment: The server on which  it is possible to play the game.

@graph.rdfs:label: hasBroadcastChannel
@graph.rdfs:comment: A broadcast channel of a broadcast service.

@graph.rdfs:label: hasMenu
@graph.rdfs:comment: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

@graph.rdfs:label: inLanguage
@graph.rdfs:comment: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[availableLanguage]].

@graph.rdfs:label: incentiveCompensation
@graph.rdfs:comment: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

@graph.rdfs:label: interactionStatistic
@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

@graph.rdfs:label: isAccessibleForFree
@graph.rdfs:comment: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

@graph.rdfs:label: isBasedOn
@graph.rdfs:comment: A resource from which this work is derived or from which it is a modification or adaptation.

@graph.rdfs:label: itemOffered
@graph.rdfs:comment: An item being offered (or demanded). The transactional nature of the offer or demand is documented using [[businessFunction]], e.g. sell, lease etc. While several common expected types are listed explicitly in this definition, others can be used. Using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

@graph.rdfs:label: jobBenefits
@graph.rdfs:comment: Description of benefits associated with the job.

@graph.rdfs:label: mainEntity
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

@graph.rdfs:label: mainEntityOfPage
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main entity being described. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#mainEntityBackground) for details.

@graph.rdfs:label: makesOffer
@graph.rdfs:comment: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

@graph.rdfs:label: offeredBy
@graph.rdfs:comment: A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

@graph.rdfs:label: parent
@graph.rdfs:comment: A parent of this person.

@graph.rdfs:label: partOfSeries
@graph.rdfs:comment: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

@graph.rdfs:label: paymentDueDate
@graph.rdfs:comment: The date that payment is due.

@graph.rdfs:label: performTime
@graph.rdfs:comment: The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

@graph.rdfs:label: performer
@graph.rdfs:comment: A performer at the event—for example, a presenter, musician, musical group or actor.

@graph.rdfs:label: photo
@graph.rdfs:comment: A photograph of this place.

@graph.rdfs:label: provider
@graph.rdfs:comment: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

@graph.rdfs:label: providesBroadcastService
@graph.rdfs:comment: The BroadcastService offered on this channel.

@graph.rdfs:label: recipeIngredient
@graph.rdfs:comment: An ingredient or ordered list of ingredients and potentially quantities used in the recipe, e.g. 1 cup of sugar, flour or garlic.  The ingredients can be represented as free text or more structured values.

@graph.rdfs:label: recordedAs
@graph.rdfs:comment: An audio recording of the work.

@graph.rdfs:label: recordedAt
@graph.rdfs:comment: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

@graph.rdfs:label: recordedIn
@graph.rdfs:comment: The CreativeWork that captured all or part of this Event.

@graph.rdfs:label: recordingOf
@graph.rdfs:comment: The composition this track is a recording of.

@graph.rdfs:label: releaseOf
@graph.rdfs:comment: The album this is a release of.

@graph.rdfs:label: review
@graph.rdfs:comment: A review of the item.

@graph.rdfs:label: roleName
@graph.rdfs:comment: A role played, performed or filled by a person or organization. For example, the team of creators for a comic book might fill the roles named 'inker', 'penciller', and 'letterer'; or an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

@graph.rdfs:label: runtimePlatform
@graph.rdfs:comment: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (example: Java v1, Python 2.3, .NET Framework 3.0).

@graph.rdfs:label: season
@graph.rdfs:comment: A season in a media series.

@graph.rdfs:label: serialNumber
@graph.rdfs:comment: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

@graph.rdfs:label: serviceArea
@graph.rdfs:comment: The geographic area where the service is provided.

@graph.rdfs:label: serviceOutput
@graph.rdfs:comment: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: sibling
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sibling of the person.

@graph.rdfs:label: significantLink
@graph.rdfs:comment: One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

@graph.rdfs:label: softwareRequirements
@graph.rdfs:comment: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

@graph.rdfs:label: sponsor
@graph.rdfs:comment: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. E.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

@graph.rdfs:label: subOrganization
@graph.rdfs:comment: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

@graph.rdfs:label: subjectOf
@graph.rdfs:comment: A CreativeWork or Event about this Thing.

@graph.rdfs:label: suggestedAnswer
@graph.rdfs:comment: An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

@graph.rdfs:label: superEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

@graph.rdfs:label: targetCollection
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

@graph.rdfs:label: track
@graph.rdfs:comment: A music recording (track)—usually a single song. If an ItemList is given, the list should contain items of type MusicRecording.

@graph.rdfs:label: warranty
@graph.rdfs:comment: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

@graph.rdfs:label: workExample
@graph.rdfs:comment: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. E.g. the paperback edition, first edition, or e-book.

@graph.rdfs:label: yield
@graph.rdfs:comment: The quantity that results by performing instructions. For example, a paper airplane, 10 personalized candles.

@graph.rdfs:label: about
@graph.rdfs:comment: The subject matter of the content.

@graph.rdfs:label: competitor
@graph.rdfs:comment: A competitor in a sports event.

@graph.rdfs:label: containedInPlace
@graph.rdfs:comment: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

@graph.rdfs:label: encoding
@graph.rdfs:comment: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

@graph.rdfs:label: hasMap
@graph.rdfs:comment: A URL to a map of the place.

@graph.rdfs:label: image
@graph.rdfs:comment: An image of the item. This can be a [[URL]] or a fully described [[ImageObject]].

@graph.rdfs:label: material
@graph.rdfs:comment: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

@graph.rdfs:label: memberOf
@graph.rdfs:comment: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

@graph.rdfs:label: parentOrganization
@graph.rdfs:comment: The larger organization that this organization is a [[subOrganization]] of, if any.

@graph.rdfs:label: result
@graph.rdfs:comment: The result produced in the action. E.g. John wrote *a book*.

@graph.rdfs:label: seller
@graph.rdfs:comment: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

@graph.rdfs:label: step
@graph.rdfs:comment: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection.

@graph.rdfs:label: subEvent
@graph.rdfs:comment: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

@graph.rdfs:label: supply
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.

@graph.rdfs:label: areaServed
@graph.rdfs:comment: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

@graph.rdfs:label: includedInDataCatalog
@graph.rdfs:comment: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

@graph.rdfs:label: member
@graph.rdfs:comment: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

@graph.rdfs:label: recipient
@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

@graph.rdfs:label: hasPart
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that is part of this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense).

@graph.rdfs:label: isPartOf
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

@graph.rdfs:label: position
@graph.rdfs:comment: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

@graph.rdfs:label: instrument
@graph.rdfs:comment: The object that helped the agent perform the action. E.g. John wrote a book with *a pen*.

@graph.rdfs:label: object
@graph.rdfs:comment: The object upon which the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). E.g. John read *a book*.

@graph.rdfs:label: location
@graph.rdfs:comment: The location of, for example, where an event is happening, where an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

@graph.rdfs:label: participant
@graph.rdfs:comment: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. E.g. John wrote a book with *Steve*.

@graph.rdfs:label: ActiveActionStatus
@graph.rdfs:comment: An in-progress action (e.g., while watching the movie, or driving to a location).

@graph.rdfs:label: AlbumRelease
@graph.rdfs:comment: AlbumRelease.

@graph.rdfs:label: AllWheelDriveConfiguration
@graph.rdfs:comment: All-wheel Drive is a transmission layout where the engine drives all four wheels.

@graph.rdfs:label: AudiobookFormat
@graph.rdfs:comment: Book format: Audiobook. This is an enumerated value for use with the bookFormat property. There is also a type 'Audiobook' in the bib extension which includes Audiobook specific properties.

@graph.rdfs:label: BackOrder
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the item is available on back order.

@graph.rdfs:label: BroadcastRelease
@graph.rdfs:comment: BroadcastRelease.

@graph.rdfs:label: CDFormat
@graph.rdfs:comment: CDFormat.

@graph.rdfs:label: CassetteFormat
@graph.rdfs:comment: CassetteFormat.

@graph.rdfs:label: CoOp
@graph.rdfs:comment: Play mode: CoOp. Co-operative games, where you play on the same team with friends.

@graph.rdfs:label: CommentPermission
@graph.rdfs:comment: Permission to add comments to the document.

@graph.rdfs:label: CompilationAlbum
@graph.rdfs:comment: CompilationAlbum.

@graph.rdfs:label: CompletedActionStatus
@graph.rdfs:comment: An action that has already taken place.

@graph.rdfs:label: DJMixAlbum
@graph.rdfs:comment: DJMixAlbum.

@graph.rdfs:label: DVDFormat
@graph.rdfs:comment: DVDFormat.

@graph.rdfs:label: DamagedCondition
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the item is damaged.

@graph.rdfs:label: DemoAlbum
@graph.rdfs:comment: DemoAlbum.

@graph.rdfs:label: DiabeticDiet
@graph.rdfs:comment: A diet appropriate for people with diabetes.

@graph.rdfs:label: DigitalAudioTapeFormat
@graph.rdfs:comment: DigitalAudioTapeFormat.

@graph.rdfs:label: DigitalFormat
@graph.rdfs:comment: DigitalFormat.

@graph.rdfs:label: Discontinued
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the item has been discontinued.

@graph.rdfs:label: EBook
@graph.rdfs:comment: Book format: Ebook.

@graph.rdfs:label: EPRelease
@graph.rdfs:comment: EPRelease.

@graph.rdfs:label: EventCancelled
@graph.rdfs:comment: The event has been cancelled. If the event has multiple startDate values, all are assumed to be cancelled. Either startDate or previousStartDate may be used to specify the event's cancelled date(s).

@graph.rdfs:label: EventMovedOnline
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the event was changed to allow online participation. See [[eventAttendanceMode]] for specifics of whether it is now fully or partially online.

@graph.rdfs:label: EventPostponed
@graph.rdfs:comment: The event has been postponed and no new date has been set. The event's previousStartDate should be set.

@graph.rdfs:label: EventRescheduled
@graph.rdfs:comment: The event has been rescheduled. The event's previousStartDate should be set to the old date and the startDate should be set to the event's new date. (If the event has been rescheduled multiple times, the previousStartDate property may be repeated.)

@graph.rdfs:label: EventScheduled
@graph.rdfs:comment: The event is taking place or has taken place on the startDate as scheduled. Use of this value is optional, as it is assumed by default.

@graph.rdfs:label: FailedActionStatus
@graph.rdfs:comment: An action that failed to complete. The action's error property and the HTTP return code contain more information about the failure.

@graph.rdfs:label: False
@graph.rdfs:comment: The boolean value false.

@graph.rdfs:label: Female
@graph.rdfs:comment: The female gender.

@graph.rdfs:label: FourWheelDriveConfiguration
@graph.rdfs:comment: Four-wheel drive is a transmission layout where the engine primarily drives two wheels with a part-time four-wheel drive capability.

@graph.rdfs:label: Friday
@graph.rdfs:comment: The day of the week between Thursday and Saturday.

@graph.rdfs:label: FrontWheelDriveConfiguration
@graph.rdfs:comment: Front-wheel drive is a transmission layout where the engine drives the front wheels.

@graph.rdfs:label: GlutenFreeDiet
@graph.rdfs:comment: A diet exclusive of gluten.

@graph.rdfs:label: GroupBoardingPolicy
@graph.rdfs:comment: The airline boards by groups based on check-in time, priority, etc.

@graph.rdfs:label: HalalDiet
@graph.rdfs:comment: A diet conforming to Islamic dietary practices.

@graph.rdfs:label: Hardcover
@graph.rdfs:comment: Book format: Hardcover.

@graph.rdfs:label: HearingImpairedSupported
@graph.rdfs:comment: Uses devices to support users with hearing impairments.

@graph.rdfs:label: HinduDiet
@graph.rdfs:comment: A diet conforming to Hindu dietary practices, in particular, beef-free.

@graph.rdfs:label: InStock
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the item is in stock.

@graph.rdfs:label: InStoreOnly
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the item is available only at physical locations.

@graph.rdfs:label: ItemListOrderAscending
@graph.rdfs:comment: An ItemList ordered with lower values listed first.

@graph.rdfs:label: ItemListOrderDescending
@graph.rdfs:comment: An ItemList ordered with higher values listed first.

@graph.rdfs:label: ItemListUnordered
@graph.rdfs:comment: An ItemList ordered with no explicit order.

@graph.rdfs:label: KosherDiet
@graph.rdfs:comment: A diet conforming to Jewish dietary practices.

@graph.rdfs:label: LaserDiscFormat
@graph.rdfs:comment: LaserDiscFormat.

@graph.rdfs:label: LeftHandDriving
@graph.rdfs:comment: The steering position is on the left side of the vehicle (viewed from the main direction of driving).

@graph.rdfs:label: LimitedAvailability
@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the item has limited availability.

@graph.rdfs:label: LiveAlbum
@graph.rdfs:comment: LiveAlbum.

@graph.rdfs:label: LockerDelivery
@graph.rdfs:comment: A DeliveryMethod in which an item is made available via locker.

@graph.rdfs:label: LowCalorieDiet
